n%20this%20one%2C%20separate%20bedrooms%20for%20married%20couples%20is%2C%20indeed%2C%20a%20growing%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20best%20friends%20always%20reminds%20me%20how%20he%20has%20a%20separate%20bedroom%20from%20his%20wife.%20They%20both%20have%20learned%20to%20love%20it.%20They%20have%20been%20married%20for%20almost%2040%20years%20and%20are%2010%20years%20into%20their%20decision%20to%20have%20different%20bedrooms.%20He%20says%20they%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20at%20home%20because%20of%20their%20work%20schedule%2C%20so%20having%20separate%20rooms%20was%20just%20what%20they%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202017%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fnation%2F2020%2F02%2F09%2Fseparate-beds-married-couples-can-help-relationship-experts-say%2F4657215002%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20conducted%20by%20the%20National%20Sleep%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2025%25%20of%20married%20couples%20sleep%20in%20separate%20rooms.%20At%20some%20point%2C%20this%20situation%20was%20given%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bsleep%20divorce%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20rubs%20me%20the%20wrong%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhy%20do%20people%20believe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterabled-couple-squirmy-grubs-sex-life-marriage-relationship-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarried%20couples%3C%2Fa%3E%20must%20be%20attached%20at%20the%20hip%3F%20I%20think%20it's%20perfectly%20fine%20to%20get%20a%20little%20break%20from%20one%20another.%20If%20the%20marriage%20is%20healthy%2C%20a%20few%20extra%20hours%20apart%20isn't%20going%20to%20rock%20the%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20can%20only%20see%20the%20benefits%20of%20having%20separate%20bedrooms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20plenty%20of%20legitimate%20reasons%20for%20sleeping%20in%20different%20bedrooms%2C%20and%20it%20is%20not%20just%20about%20having%20a%20break%20from%20my%20wife%20and%20needing%20some%20personal%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20I%20can%20only%20see%20how%20it%20would%20improve%20our%20sleeping.%20For%20instance%2C%20my%20wife%20goes%20to%20bed%20at%20least%20two%20hours%20before%20me%20every%20night%2C%20and%20I%20worry%20about%20waking%20her%20up%20when%20I%20finally%20get%20into%20bed.%20Plus%2C%20when%20I%20do%20get%20to%20sleep%2C%20I%20snore%20loudly%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fhow-to-treat-sleep-apnea%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSleep%2520apnea%2520is%2520a%2520common%2Cand%2520get%2520the%2520proper%2520treatment.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20have%20sleep%20apnea%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20makes%20her%20wake%20me%20up%20so%20I%20can%20stop%20snoring%20so%20she%20can%20go%20back%20to%20sleep.%20It%20is%20a%20never-ending%2C%20frustrating%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20also%20have%20different%20ideas%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-mattress%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperfect%20mattress%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20the%20right%20temperature%20at%20night.%20If%20we%20had%20our%20own%20bedroom%2C%20we%20would%20be%20more%20suited%20to%20our%20own%20preferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20can%20this%20do%20anything%20except%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchanges-to-make-in-your-marriage-according-to-experts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eimprove%20our%20marriage%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20We%20will%20have%20a%20little%20alone%20time%3B%20I%20believe%20absence%20makes%20the%20heart%20grow%20fonder.%20We%20will%20also%20both%20be%20much%20better%20rested.%20Plus%2C%20we%20can%20watch%20our%20own%20programs%20and%20listen%20to%20our%20own%20podcasts%20without%20having%20noise-canceling%20headphones%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20my%20wife%20isn't%20convinced%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20claims%20we%20have%20to%20share%20a%20bedroom%20to%20talk%20at%20the%20end%20of%20every%20day%20and%20share%20our%20thoughts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20we%20have%20been%20together%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpsychologist-realized-problem-toxic-relationships-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edating%20and%20marriage%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20for%20almost%2010%20years%2C%20so%20I%20can't%20imagine%20having%20anything%20new%20to%20discuss.%20I%20am%20like%20that%20old-time%20stand-up%20comedian%20doing%20the%20same%20old%20routine%20without%20any%20new%20material%20for%20the%20last%20few%20years.%20We%20aren't%20discussing%20anything%20important%20in%20bed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20night.%20We%20might%20share%20a%20story%20about%20what%20one%20of%20the%20kids%20did%20during%20the%20day%2C%20make%20a%20remark%20about%20adding%20something%20to%20the%20grocery%20list%2C%20and%20have%20a%20little%20small%20talk%20about%20what%20happened%20at%20work%20that%20day.%20Nothing%20earth-shattering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20aren't%20solving%20the%20problems%20of%20the%20world.%20We%20aren't%20even%20solving%20our%20own%20problems.%20We%20are%20just%20making%20chitchat%20before%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20separate%20bathrooms%20worked%20so%20perfectly%3B%20I%20just%20wish%20my%20wife%20would%20be%20convinced%20to%20take%20it%20one%20step%20further%20so%20I%20could%20relax%20and%20fall%20asleep%20in%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseparate-bedrooms-couple-split-sleep-divorce-trend-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709381041000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e0a299ce7f1785b2e4e3f5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseparate-bedrooms-couple-split-sleep-divorce-trend-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20couple%20is%20split%20over%20separate%20bedrooms.%20The%20husband%20knows%20%26quot%3Bsleep%20divorce%26quot%3