41152%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-08-at-1.00.13-PM.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20brutality%20during%20the%20recent%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%20has%20been%20more%20intense%20than%20the%202020%20protests.%20Three%20farmers%20reportedly%20lost%20their%20vision%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh%2Fat-least-3-farmers-lost-vision-due-to-pellet-injuries-punjab-health-minister-9164170%2F%5C%22%3Eas%20a%20result%20of%20pellet%20gun%20injuries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20several%20had%20their%20faces%20disfigured%20by%20the%20gunshots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShubkaran%20Singh%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20farmer%20from%20Bhatinda%2C%20died%20from%20head%20injuries%20last%20week%2C%20with%20his%20family%20and%20farmer%20groups%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fnews%2Fcrime%2Fshubhkaran-singh-death-bullet-injury-farmers-protest-fir-details%5C%22%3Emaintaining%20he%20was%20shot.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Much%20before%20the%20protests%20began%2C%20the%20Haryana%20Police%E2%80%99s%20preparations%20gave%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20far%20the%20state%20would%20go%20to%20prevent%20a%20movement%20from%20taking%20shape.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20DGP%20of%20Haryana%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fharyana-dgp-denies-using-pellet-guns-against-protesting-farmers%2Farticle67860605.ece%5C%22%3Edenied%20using%20pellets%20on%20farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20medical%20injuries%20sustained%20give%20us%20a%20picture%20of%20the%20spectacular%20nature%20of%20violence%20against%20farmers%20protesting%20peacefully%20at%20the%20Punjab-Haryana%20border%20crossings%20of%20Khanuari%20and%20Shambhu%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20instance%20of%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20in%20India%20was%20witnessed%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20in%202010.%20In%202016%2C%20following%20the%20protests%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20after%20the%20encounter%20of%20Hizbul%20commander%20Burhan%20Wani%2C%20the%20police%20resorted%20to%20excessive%20pellet%20actions%2C%20injuring%20hundreds%20of%20protesters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20a%20petition%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20High%20Court%20regarding%20the%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%2C%20and%20the%20court%20refused%20to%20put%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20its%20use.%20In%20the%20year%202017%2C%20the%20Jammu%20%26amp%3B%20Kashmir%20Bar%20Association%20petitioned%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20for%20a%20blanket%20prohibition%20on%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20weapons%2C%20which%20asked%20the%20high%20court%20to%20expedite%20the%20matter.%20It%20was%20in%202020%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tribuneindia.com%2Fnews%2Fj-k%2Fj-k-high-court-refuses-to-ban-use-of-pellet-guns-in-kashmir-53869%5C%22%3Ehigh%20court%20finally%20dismissed%20the%20petition%3C%2Fa%3E%20upholding%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20by%20the%20security%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20reasoned%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20protest%20is%20not%20peaceful%20and%20security%20personnel%20are%20attacked%20by%20violent%20mobs%2C%20they%20have%20to%20use%20force%20in%20self-defense.%E2%80%9D%20Further%2C%20regarding%20the%20nature%20of%20force%2C%20it%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20kind%20of%20force%20has%20to%20be%20used%20at%20a%20relevant%20point%20in%20time%20or%20in%20a%20given%20situation%20and%20place%20has%20to%20be%20decided%20by%20the%20persons%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20place%20where%20the%20attack%20is%20happening.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20rejected%20the%20appeal%20by%20referring%20to%20force%20mostly%20in%20vague%20terms%20without%20addressing%20the%20issue%20of%20pellets.%20However%2C%20it%20mentioned%20that%20the%20Union%20of%20India%20has%20formed%20an%20expert%20committee%20to%20look%20into%20the%20matter.%20The%20report%2C%20which%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20made%20public%2C%20did%20not%20prohibit%20its%20usage%20but%20recommended%20that%20it%20be%20used%20as%20a%20last%20resort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20is%20now%20pending%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20heard%20in%20April%20this%20year.%20The%20petition%20challenges%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20on%20account%20of%20them%20being%20%E2%80%98indiscriminatory%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20very%20nature%20of%20how%20they%20target%20people.%20What%20is%20meant%20by%20this%20%E2%80%98indiscriminate%E2%80%99%20nature%20is%20that%20when%20a%20pellet%20gun%20is%20fired%2C%20100%20pellets%20that%20are%20lethal%20are%20sprayed%20in%20all%20directions%2C%20where%20men%2C%20women%2C%20children%2C%20and%20even%20innocent%20bystanders%20watching%20the%20events%20are%20blinded%2C%20injured%2C%20and%20sometimes%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoctors%20treating%20pellet%20victims%20have%20stated%20that%20it%20maims%20a%20person%20forever%2C%20causing%20partial%20or%20complete%20blindness.%20The%20spread%20and%20proclivity%20for%20their%20usage%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20degree%20of%20destruction%20caused%2C%20are%20unparalleled%2C%20making%20them%20unsuitable%20for%20managing%20the%20crowd%20as%20their%20operators%20cannot%20effectively%20control%20their%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20%E2%80%98indiscriminate%E2%80%99%20character%20of%20pellets%20violates%20the%20UN%20Basic%20Principles%2C%20which%20specify%20that%20the%20use%20of%20force%20to%20disperse%20nonviolent%20unlawful%20assemblies%20should%20be%20avoided.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDissecting%20the%20pellet%20and%20the%20law%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPellet%20guns%2C%20made%20of%20metals%20that%20resemble%20ball%20bearings%2C%20are%20classified%20as%20Kinetic%20Impact%20Projectiles%20(KIPs)%2C%20which%20include%20weapons%20that%20cannot%20be%20aimed%20at%20specific%20targets%20but%20scatter%20ammunition%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20risks%20connected%20with%20KIPs%20include%20death%20or%20major%20injury%20to%20the%20head%2C%20upper%20body%2C%20or%20susceptible%20area%20if%20struck%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20projectiles%20penetrating%20the%20body%2C%20and%20a%20high%20risk%20of%20injuring%20innocent%20bystanders%20due%20to%20projectile%20inaccuracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20international%20law%2C%20the%20use%20of%20pellets%20is%20prohibited%20because%20it%20violates%20the%20norms%20of%20proportionality%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law%20and%20customary%20international%20law.%20The%20UN%20Basic%20Principles%20on%20the%20Use%20of%20Force%20and%20Firearms%20by%20Law%20Enforcement%20Officials%2C%20adopted%20by%20the%20eighth%20United%20Nations%20Congress%20on%20Crime%20Prevention%20and%20Treatment%20of%20Offenders%20require%20the%20government%20and%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20consider%20the%20ethical%20issues%20associated%20with%20the%20use%20of%20force%20and%20firearms%2C%20as%20well%20as%20to%20exercise%20restraint%20proportionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fharyana-dgp-claims-rubber-bullets-not-pellet-guns-used-on-protesting-farmers%5C%22%3EHaryana%20DGP%20Claims%20Rubber%20Bullets%2C%20Not%20Pellet%20Guns%2C%20Used%20on%20Protesting%20Farmers%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20the%20development%20of%20non-lethal%20incapacitating%20weapons%20for%20use%20in%20specific%20scenarios.%20Interestingly%2C%20the%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross%2C%20under%20rules%2070%20and%2071%2C%20prohibits%20the%20use%20of%20tools%20that%20are%20indiscriminate%20and%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20cause%20unnecessary%20pain%20or%20suffering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20International%20Committee%20of%20the%20Red%20Cross%20rules%2C%20even%20for%20warfare%2C%20do%20not%20accept%20attacks%20that%20may%20cause%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%2C%20injury%20to%20civilians%2C%20damage%20to%20civilian%20objects%2C%20or%20a%20combination%20thereof%20that%20is%20excessive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPellet%20action%20against%20the%20farmers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20are%20likewise%20constitutionally%20obligated%20to%20display%20fundamental%20restraint%20and%20act%20proportionally%20to%20their%20legitimate%20objectives%20that%20are%20to%20be%20achieved.%20It%20is%20consequently%20crucial%20to%20ask%20what%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20objective%20was%20in%20using%20force%20against%20the%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAssuming%20it%20was%20to%20prevent%20the%20farmers%20from%20marching%20to%20Delhi%2C%20then%20the%20question%20remains%3A%20what%20if%20the%20farmers%20had%20crossed%20the%20border%20and%20arrived%20in%20Delhi%3F%20Have%20the%20farmers%20not%20demonstrated%20enough%20that%20their%20protests%20have%20been%20extremely%20peaceful%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20is%20completely%20aware%20that%20the%20protests%20are%20not%20intended%20to%20generate%20a%20public%20emergency%20or%20chaos%20in%20Delhi.%20The%202020%20farmer%20demonstrations%20have%20already%20given%20us%20the%20most%20powerful%20example%20of%20non-violent%20protests%20in%20the%20recent%20history%20of%20India.%20What%20explains%20the%20firing%20of%20tear%20gas%20shells%20from%20drones%20overhead%2C%20injuring%20hundreds%20of%20farmers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20are%20elderly%20and%20have%20difficulty%20breathing%2C%20when%20a%20template%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20protest%20had%20already%20been%20established%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20question%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20asked%20here%20is%3A%20Was%20the%20use%20of%20cranes%2C%20boulders%2C%20and%20roadblocks%20to%20restrict%20the%20protestors%E2%80%99%20from%20exercising%20their%20constitutional%20rights%20to%20freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20assembly%20not%20a%20force%20that%20the%20state%20performed%20right%20before%20the%20protests%20had%20begun%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20deploying%20pellet%20guns%20that%20left%20protesters%20permanently%20disabled%20and%20at%20risk%20of%20death%2C%20the%20state%20breached%20its%20commitment%20to%20protect%20and%20preserve%20human%20life.%20These%20violated%20both%20the%20constitutional%20requirement%20to%20protect%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights%20to%20life%20and%20health%20as%20well%20as%20the%20international%20laws%20that%20forbid%20such%20use%20in%20conflict%2C%20let%20alone%20in%20peaceful%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20Prevention%20Act%20(UAPA)%20is%20widely%20used%20to%20discredit%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%2C%20and%20it%20has%20become%20a%20standard%20instrument%20for%20criminalising%20dissent%20in%20democratic%20India.%20It%20is%20time%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20not%20let%20the%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%20be%20normalised%20in%20a%20peaceful%20citizen%20demonstration.%20Suppressing%20people%E2%80%99s%20movement%20with%20measures%20such%20as%20pellet%20guns%20assumes%20protestors%20are%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fem%3Eviolent%20and%20unorganised%20mob%E2%80%99%20and%20attempts%20to%20disorganise%20an%20organised%20group%20of%20civilian%20protestors%20by%20using%20excessive%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20must%20see%20through%20the%20recent%20usage%20of%20pellet%20guns%20in%20Manipur%20and%20Delhi%20borders%20against%20the%20protestors%20and%20strike%20it%20down%20immediately.%20It%20must%20now%20hear%20the%20long-overdue%20petition%20and%20prohibit%20the%20use%20of%20pellet%20guns%20altogether%2C%20especially%20during%20civilian%20protests.%20This%20would%20reassert%20its%20constitutional%20obligation%20to%20protect%20and%20facilitate%20free%20expression%20and%20assembly%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20a%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709380750000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F08141152%2FWhatsApp-Image-2024-02-08-at-1.00.13-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffarmers-protest-has-shown-that-sc-must-strike-down-the-use-of-pellet-guns-with-a-sense-of-urgency%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20international%20law%2C%20the%20use%20of%20pellets%20is%20prohibited%20because%20it%20violates%20the%20norms%20of%20proportionality%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law%20and%20customary%20international%20law.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffarmers-protest-has-shown-that-sc-must-strike-down-the-use-of-pellet-guns-with-a-sense-of-urgency%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk%20just%20threw%20down%20the%20gauntlet%20at%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20and%20there's%20no%20going%20back%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20and%20Sam%20Altman%20facing%20off%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e2094990413ab8e1d84c9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENathan%20Howard%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%20is%20suing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-openai-company-chatgpt-elon-musk-founded-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20its%20CEO%2C%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20years%20after%20leaving%20the%20startup.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20Musk's%20allegations%2C%20legal%20experts%20say%20his%20case%20against%20OpenAI%20appears%20weak.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20Musk's%20lawsuit%20could%20still%20hamper%20OpenAI%2C%20tying%20it%20up%20in%20court%20and%20airing%20dirty%20laundry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20last%20May%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-ceo-elon-musk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20sitting%20down%20for%20an%20interview%20with%20CNBC's%20David%20Faber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI%2C%20Musk%20grew%20visibly%20frustrated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20wouldn't%20exist%20without%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DbWr-DA5Wjfw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20does%20seem%20weird%20that%20something%20can%20be%20a%20nonprofit%2C%20open-source%20and%20somehow%20transform%20itself%20into%20a%20for-profit%2C%20closed%20source%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20exact%20opposite%20of%20what%20I%20gave%20them%20the%20money%20for.%20Is%20that%20legal%3F%20It%20doesn't%20seem%20legal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20answer%20may%20have%20been%20the%20writing%20on%20the%20wall%20that%20the%20billionaire%20was%20ready%20to%20take%20Altman%20and%20OpenAI%20to%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-sues-sam-altman-betrays-openai-mission-chatgpt-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMusk%20sued%20OpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20its%20CEO%2C%20claiming%20that%20the%20company's%20partnership%20with%20Microsoft%20violated%20its%20mission%20by%20putting%20profit%20ahead%20of%20creating%20open-source%20technology%20that%20would%20benefit%20humanity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-elon-musk-and-sam-altman-relationship-feuds-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeefed%20before%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Altman%20had%20been%20more%20diplomatic%20in%20his%20answers%20publicly%20when%20asked%20about%20Musk%2C%20even%20calling%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-elon-musk-open-ai-chatgpt-twitter-attack-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20hero%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20now%2C%20Musk%20has%20thrown%20down%20the%20gauntlet%2C%20likely%20marking%20a%20point%20of%20no%20return%20for%20their%20relationship%20as%20he%20seeks%20in%20his%20lawsuit%20to%20force%20OpenAI%20to%20make%20its%20research%20and%20technology%20open-source%2C%20cut%20off%20Microsoft%20from%20GPT-4%2C%20and%20prevent%20Altman%20and%20Microsoft%20from%20benefiting%20from%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20he's%20trying%20to%20slow%20them%20down%20so%20he%20can%20catch%20up%20on%20his%20own%20efforts%2C%26quot%3B%20Kyle%20Lawrence%2C%20a%20corporate%20and%20securities%20lawyer%20at%20Falcon%20Rappaport%20%26amp%3B%20Berkman%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20how%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20big%20tech%20giants%20operate.%20They%20succeed%20by%20throttling%20other%20institution's%20ability%20to%20move%20forward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20Musk%20is%20far%20from%20a%20disinterested%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20lawsuit%20comes%20after%20the%20billionaire%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-new-company-xai-website-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%20his%20own%20AI%20company%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year.%20Musk%20has%20said%20he%20invested%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20into%20OpenAI%20during%20its%20founding%20but%20walked%20away%20from%20the%20company's%20board%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20Musk%20said%20he'd%20left%20to%20avoid%20a%20potential%20conflict%20of%20interest%20with%20Tesla%20and%20its%20AI%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20weak%20case%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20Musk's%20grandstanding%2C%20his%20case%20against%20OpenAI%20appears%20shaky%20at%20best%2C%20David%20Hoffman%2C%20a%20contract%20law%20expert%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20very%20difficult%20to%20claim%20a%20breach%20of%20contract%20without%20a%20written%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoffman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20case%20argues%20that%20OpenAI%20has%20strayed%20from%20its%20%26quot%3Bfounding%20agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20there%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20be%20such%20a%20written%20agreement.%20The%20complaint%20relies%20on%20unwritten%20contract%20claims%2C%20which%20will%20be%20difficult%20to%20hold%20up%20in%20a%20court%20of%20law%2C%20Hoffman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Musk's%20case%20cites%20an%20email%20from%20Altman%20(which%20appears%20to%20be%20more%20of%20a%20casual%20negotiation%20than%20a%20contract)%20and%20the%20OpenAI's%20certificate%20of%20incorporation%20(which%20Musk%20didn't%20sign%20and%20doesn't%20mention%20keeping%20the%20company%20open%20source).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20because%20OpenAI%20is%20a%20non-profit%20it%20will%20be%20difficult%20for%20the%20billionaire%20to%20claim%20OpenAI's%20board%20has%20any%20fiduciary%20duties%20to%20him%2C%20Samuel%20Brunson%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20legal%20expert%20from%20Loyola%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire's%20argument%20regarding%20OpenAI's%20failure%20to%20act%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bbenefit%20of%20humanity%26quot%3B%20is%20more%20of%20a%20philosophical%20one%20than%20a%20tangible%20legal%20argument%2C%20Kyle%20Lawrence%2C%20a%20corporate%20and%20securities%20lawyer%20from%20Falcon%20Rappaport%20%26amp%3B%20Berkman%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWho's%20to%20say%20that%20what%20they're%20doing%20isn't%20benefiting%20humanity%3F%26quot%3B%20Lawrence%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20could%20easily%20say%20they%20need%20a%20billion%20dollars%20to%20do%20that%2C%20and%20who's%20to%20say%20that%20the%20mechanism%20they%20put%20in%20place%20to%20get%20that%20billion%20dollars%20is%20in%20conflict%20with%20their%20goal%20of%20benefiting%20humanity%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOpenAI%20could%20pay%20a%20hefty%20price%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20experts%20say%20it's%20unlikely%20Musk's%20case%20would%20succeed%2C%20OpenAI%20may%20still%20pay%20a%20price.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20types%20of%20lawsuits%20can%20air%20a%20lot%20of%20dirty%20laundry%20and%20it%20can%20be%20a%20major%20distraction%20that%20could%20impact%20their%20day-to-day%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20Hoffman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20publicity%20around%20the%20lawsuit%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20Musk%20wins%20or%20loses%20%E2%80%94%20could%20also%20damage%20OpenAI's%20reputation%20%E2%80%94%20fueling%20the%20fire%20lit%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-sam-altman-did-so-bad-he-got-fired-openai-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAltman%20was%20briefly%20ousted%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20men%20in%20the%20world%2C%20Musk%20could%20tie%20OpenAI%20up%20in%20litigation%20for%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Lawrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20could%20also%20set%20a%20dangerous%20standard%20%E2%80%94%20if%20Musk%20were%20to%20pull%20out%20a%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Musk%20were%20to%20win%20this%20case%2C%20it%20would%20set%20a%20bad%20precedent%20for%20non-profits%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Brunson%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20could%20start%20seeing%20a%20bunch%20of%20disaffected%20donors%20coming%20forward%20trying%20to%20get%20their%20money%20back%2C%20and%20most%20nonprofits%20don't%20have%20the%20same%20resources%20as%20OpenAI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-throws-down-gauntlet-sam-altman-openai-lawsuit-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709380681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e209736080194819fba5ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-throws-down-gauntlet-sam-altman-openai-lawsuit-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elon%20Musk's%20case%20against%20OpenAI%20may%20be%20weak%2C%20but%20the%20AI%20venture%20could%20still%20pay%20a%20hefty%20price%2C%20experts%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gkay%40insider.com%20(Grace%20Kay)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-throws-down-gauntlet-sam-altman-openai-lawsuit-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20Honourable%20Exit%3F%20Why%20Two%20BJP%20MPs%20Said%20They%20Don't%20Want%20To%20Contest%20Again%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20Indian%20politics%2C%20where%20there%20is%20intense%20competition%20for%20tickets%20from%20any%20party%20that%20has%20a%20chance%20of%20winning%2C%20sitting%20MPs%20declaring%20that%20they%20do%20not%20want%20to%20contest%20again%20is%20rare.%20So%2C%20when%20two%20BJP%20MPs%20said%20-%20within%20hours%20of%20each%20other%20-%20today%20that%20they%20would%20like%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Brelieved%26quot%3B%20of%20their%20political%20duties%2C%20it%20took%20many%20by%20surprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20have%20told%20NDTV%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20well-oiled%20election%20machinery%20of%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20has%20conducted%20extensive%20surveys%20and%20held%20long%20deliberations%20on%20every%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%2C%20had%20already%20decided%20not%20to%20repeat%20Gautam%20Gambhir%20and%20Jayant%20Sinha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20X%20around%2010%20am%20today%2C%20Gautam%20Gambhir%2C%20the%20BJP%20MP%20from%20East%20Delhi%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20requested%20Hon'ble%20Party%20President%20%40JPNadda%20ji%20to%20relieve%20me%20of%20my%20political%20duties%20so%20that%20I%20can%20focus%20on%20my%20upcoming%20cricket%20commitments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20five%20hours%20later%2C%20Jayant%20Sinha%2C%20who%20represents%20Jharkhand's%20Hazaribagh%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20made%20a%20nearly%20identical%20post.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20requested%20Hon'ble%20Party%20President%20Shri%20%40JPNadda%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0ji%20to%20relieve%20me%20of%20my%20direct%20electoral%20duties%20so%20that%20I%20can%20focus%20my%20efforts%20on%20combating%20global%20climate%20change%20in%20Bharat%20and%20around%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20leaders%20also%20thanked%20the%20party's%20leadership%2C%20including%20PM%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20for%20the%20opportunities%20provided%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGautam%20Gambhir%20is%20a%20first-time%20MP%2C%20while%20Jayant%20Sinha%2C%20son%20of%20former%20Union%20Minister%20Yashwant%20Sinha%20had%20been%20elected%20from%20Hazaribagh%20twice%20in%20a%20row.%20Sources%20indicated%20that%20both%20MPs%20were%20not%20very%20popular%20in%20their%20constituencies%20and%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20has%20set%20itself%20a%20target%20of%20winning%20a%20mammoth%20370%20seats%2C%20had%20decided%20not%20to%20repeat%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20Delhi%2C%20where%20the%20party%20had%20won%20all%20seven%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%202019%2C%20the%20party%20is%20looking%20for%20new%20faces%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20source.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20followed%20a%20lengthy%2C%20detailed%20process%2C%20which%20included%20getting%20feedback%20from%20the%20people%20in%20every%20constituency%2C%20conducting%20internal%20evaluations%2C%20and%20hiring%20survey%20agencies%20to%20file%20comprehensive%20reports.%20These%20were%20followed%20by%20deliberations%20by%20the%20state%20leadership%20and%20the%20national%20brass.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20the%20national%20leadership%20had%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20the%20MPs%20whose%20performance%20was%20not%20up%20to%20the%20mark%20would%20not%20be%20repeated%20and%20that%20at%20least%2060%20incumbent%20MPs%20could%20face%20this%20fate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%20night%2C%20a%20five-hour%20meeting%20had%20been%20held%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20was%20chaired%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20attended%20by%20Mr%20Shah%20and%20Mr%20Nadda%2C%20among%20others.%20The%20meeting%2C%20which%20began%20at%2011%20pm%20and%20ended%20at%204%20am%2C%20had%20al