n%20front%20of%20screens%20instead%20of%20doing%20other%20things.%20When%20I%20started%20digging%20into%20data%2C%20it%20all%20supported%20how%20I%20was%20already%20feeling.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fnccdphp%2Fdnpao%2Fmultimedia%2Finfographics%2Fgetmoving.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20CDC%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20that%20the%20average%20daily%20screen%20time%20for%208-year-olds%20is%20six%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20excluding%20screen%20usage%20for%20educational%20purposes.%20That's%20a%20little%20over%20114%20days%20a%20year%20spent%20staring%20at%20a%20screen%20and%20being%20sedentary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20it%20isn't%20just%20the%20huge%20chunks%20of%20my%20child's%20life%20being%20given%20to%20app%20developers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounders-disrupting-social-media-networking-landscape-new-apps-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20platforms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20people%20selling%20stuff.%20Screens%20also%20displace%20other%20activities%2C%20including%20playing%20outside%2C%20practicing%20sports%2C%20and%20connecting%20with%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20screen-free%20means%20more%20time%20to%20argue%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F4-signs-youre-not-brushing-your-teeth-correctly-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteeth-brushing%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20green%20vegetables%2C%20you%20know%2C%20the%20good%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20do%20other%20things%20instead%20of%20looking%20at%20a%20screen%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20my%20children%20aren't%20spending%20six%20hours%20a%20day%20on%20a%20screen%2C%20they%20do%20all%20sorts%20of%20other%20stuff%20%E2%80%94%20some%20of%20it%20worthy%2C%20much%20of%20it%20banal%2C%20but%20at%20least%20there's%20a%20self-directed%20ebb%20and%20flow%20to%20their%20free%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20moment%2C%20they%20read%20lots%20of%20books%2C%20learn%20about%20%26quot%3Bcool%20science%20stuff%26quot%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-spending-more-time-outside-is-healthy-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplay%20outdoors%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20eldest%20is%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20adolescence%20and%20will%20probably%20soon%20hate%20me%20for%20not%20letting%20him%20watch%20endless%20Instagram%20reels%20and%20videos.%20I'm%20also%20aware%20that%2C%20in%20raising%20my%20kids%20like%20this%2C%20I%20am%20making%20them%20uncool.%20Being%20like%20everyone%20else%20is%20the%20social%20path%20of%20least%20resistance%20through%20adolescence%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-stopped-watching-tv-for-a-week-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20being%20exposed%20to%20screens%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20positions%20my%20children%20as%20radically%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20will%20have%20screens%20eventually%2C%20but%20I'm%20putting%20them%20off%20as%20long%20as%20I%20can%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20screen%20time%20and%20kids%20is%20more%20than%20Luddite%20pearl-clutching.%20There%20is%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6214874%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMore%2520hours%2520of%2520screen%2520time%2Cin%2520ages%25202%2520to%252017.%26amp%3Btext%3DHigh%2520users%2520show%2520less%2520curiosity%2C%252Dcontrol%252C%2520and%2520emotional%2520stability.%26amp%3Btext%3DTwice%2520as%2520many%2520high%2520(vs%2Can%2520anxiety%2520or%2520depression%2520diagnosis.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20good%20data%20to%20show%20that%20high%20levels%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20screen%20time%20are%20linked%20to%20poor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fonline-therapy-for-teens%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eteen%20mental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMastery%20of%20the%20screens%20that%20will%20permeate%20their%20lives%20will%20come%20easily%20%E2%80%94%20the%20longer%20I%20can%20put%20this%20off%2C%20the%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stand%20by%20my%20decision%20to%20keep%20my%20kids%20a%20little%20weird%20and%20pretty%20uncool.%20Being%20different%20has%20long%20been%20a%20cause%20for%20bullying%2C%20but%20I%20also%20know%20that%20allowing%20my%20kids%20to%20be%20the%20same%20as%20their%20peers%20won't%20necessarily%20protect%20them%20from%20online%20or%20conventional%20bullying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hope%20that%20they%20are%20having%20a%20less%20distracted%20childhood%2C%20with%20fewer%20interruptions%20and%20less%20harmful%20input%20from%20online%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-no-screens-home-weird-regrets-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709380382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65de292b90413ab8e1d72d9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-no-screens-home-weird-regrets-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20mom%20with%20three%20kids%20under%20age%2010%20says%20they%20don't%20have%20any%20screens%20at%20home%2C%20like%20smartphones%20or%20tablets.%20She%20says%20they%20might%20be%20weird%20because%20of%20it.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Emma%20Armstrong)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-no-screens-home-weird-regrets-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Has%20Eliminated%20Extreme%20Poverty%2C%20Says%20US%20Think%20Tank%20Brookings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20think%20tank%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20in%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20lauded%20India%20for%20eliminating%20extreme%20poverty%2C%20marking%20a%20significant%20milestone%20in%20the%20nation's%20socio-economic%20landscape.%20Authored%20by%20economists%20Surjit%20Bhalla%20and%20Karan%20Bhasin%2C%20the%20report%20attributes%20the%20achievement%20to%20the%20Indian%20government's%20robust%20policy%20initiatives%20focused%20on%20redistribution%2C%20fostering%20inclusive%20growth%20throughout%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20puts%20out%20statistics%20that%20show%20a%20substantial%20decline%20in%20the%20headcount%20poverty%20ratio%20and%20a%20surge%20in%20household%20consumption.%20The%20data%20presented%20challenges%20to%20previous%20estimates%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20indicating%20a%20lower%20number%20of%20impoverished%20individuals%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20pivotal%20factors%20contributing%20to%20this%20success%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study%2C%20is%20the%20amalgamation%20of%20high%20economic%20growth%20and%20a%20significant%20reduction%20in%20income%20inequality.%20The%20'headcount%20poverty%20ratio%20at%20the%20purchase%20power%20parity%20%241.9%20level%20plummeted%20from%2012.2%25%20in%202011-12%20to%20a%20mere%202%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20asserted%20that%20the%20elevated%20consumption%20growth%20in%20rural%20areas%20is%20a%20direct%20outcome%20of%20the%20government's%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20redistribution.%20Publicly%20funded%20initiatives%2C%20such%20as%20the%20national%20mission%20for%20constructing%20toilets%20and%20the%20drive%20for%20universal%20access%20to%20electricity%2C%20modern%20cooking%20fuel%2C%20and%20piped%20water%2C%20have%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20impact%20of%20such%20policies%2C%20the%20report%20notes%20a%20staggering%20increase%20in%20rural%20access%20to%20piped%20water%20from%2016.8%25%20in%20August%202019%20to%20an%20impressive%2074.7%25%20at%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20emphasise%20that%20the%20elimination%20of%20extreme%20poverty%20in%20India%20not%20only%20heralds%20positive%20implications%20for%20global%20poverty%20rates%20but%20also%20signals%20the%20need%20for%20the%20nation%20to%20graduate%20to%20a%20higher%20poverty%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20two%20of%20the%20world's%20leading%20economies%20-%20Japan%20and%20the%20UK%20-%20have%20slipped%20into%20recession.%20Britain%20recently%20revealed%20a%200.3%20percent%20contraction%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202023%20and%20has%20officially%20entered%20a%20recession.%20Japan%2C%20once%20poised%20to%20become%20the%20world's%20largest%20economy%2C%20has%20also%20been%20struggling%20to%20recover%20after%20the%20Covid%20pandemic%20which%20crippled%20the%20country's%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spotlight%20has%20now%20turned%20on%20India%2C%20which%20has%20emerged%20as%20a%20beacon%20of%20opportunity%20for%20investors.%20Projections%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20suggest%20that%20India%20is%20poised%20to%20overtake%20both%20Japan%20and%20Germany%20in%20terms%20of%20economic%20output%2C%20with%20estimates%20placing%20the%20shift%20in%202026%20and%202027%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709380380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2F8fsttk8s_sarojini-market-delhi_625x300_02_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-has-eliminated-extreme-poverty-says-us-think-tank-brookings-5162867%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20American%20think%20tank%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20in%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20lauded%20India%20for%20eliminating%20extreme%20poverty%2C%20marking%20a%20significant%20milestone%20in%20the%20nation's%20socio-economic%20landscape.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-has-eliminated-extreme-poverty-says-us-think-tank-brookings-5162867%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampprojec