tps%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funrwa%2Ft-68109536%5C%22%3EUNRWA%3C%2Fa%3E)%20were%20involved%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20attack%20in%20Israel%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Feuropean-commission%2Ft-17455066%5C%22%3EEuropean%20Commission%3C%2Fa%3E%20suspended%C2%A0payments%20to%20the%20aid%20organisation%20for%20one%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhamas%2Ft-19034915%5C%22%3EHamas%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgermany%2Ft-17871182%5C%22%3EGermany%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20others%20designate%20as%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20%E2%80%93%20led%20an%20attack%20in%20Israel%20that%20resulted%20in%20the%20deaths%20of%20around%201%2C200%20people%20and%20the%20kidnapping%20of%20over%20200%20hostages.%20In%20response%2C%20Israel%20launched%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war%2Ft-57547294%5C%22%3Eassault%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20the%20besieged%20enclave%20which%20has%20since%20killed%20over%2030%2C000%20people%20and%20displaced%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20a%20first%20breakthrough%20deal%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20saw%20the%20release%20of%20about%20110%20hostages.%20Talks%20are%20currently%20ongoing%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20and%20the%20release%20of%20remaining%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPartial%20fund%20released%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20next%20week%2C%20the%20EU%C2%A0expects%20to%20resume%20payments%20to%20UNRWA%2C%20with%20one%20tranche%20of%20%E2%82%AC50%20million%20(%2454%20million)%2C%20followed%20by%20another%20%E2%82%AC32%20million%20split%20into%20two%20installments%20later%20in%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20after%20long%20negotiations%2C%20in%20which%20UNRWA%20had%20agreed%20to%20EU%20conditions.%20The%20United%20Nations%20launched%20an%20internal%20investigation%20into%20the%20affair%2C%20and%20the%20EU%20is%20conducting%20an%20independent%20probe%20with%20its%20own%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20exchange%20of%20correspondence%20with%20the%20EU%2C%20UNRWA%20Commissioner-General%20Philippe%20Lazzarini%20assured%20the%20Commission%20that%20his%20organisation%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20October%207%20attack%20in%20Israel%2C%20and%20that%20all%20of%20his%2013%2C000%20members%20of%20staff%20working%20in%20the%20besieged%20Gaza%20Strip%20were%20being%20reviewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20in%20a%20February%20meeting%20with%20EU%20foreign%20ministers%2C%20Lazzarini%20said%20that%20Israeli%20officials%20had%20yet%20to%20provide%20any%20evidence%20for%20the%20accusations%20leveled%20against%20the%20relief%20organisation.%20A%20UN%20spokesperson%20also%20said%20that%20they%20were%20still%20waiting%20for%20Israel%20to%20provide%20records%20or%20other%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20ongoing%20assault%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20in%20Gaza%2C%20EU%20foreign%20ministers%20recognised%20that%20UNRWA%20was%20essential%20to%20providing%20at%20least%20basic%20relief%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fgaza-how-much-humanitarian-aid-is-getting-through%2Fa-67203929%5C%22%3Ebeleaguered%20population%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEU%20boosting%20humanitarian%20aid%20through%20partners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Commission%20has%20also%20announced%20it%20would%20pledge%20an%20additional%20%E2%82%AC68%20million%20in%20emergency%20support%20for%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%2C%20to%20be%20paid%20through%20international%20aid%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20International%20Federation%20of%20Red%20Cross%20and%20Red%20Crescent%20Societies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20funds%20will%20be%20provided%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20%E2%82%AC125%20million%20already%20allotted%20for%20this%20year.%20That%20would%20bring%20the%20total%20sum%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%20for%20Palestinians%2C%20whether%20through%20UNRWA%20or%20through%20other%20international%20organizations%2C%20to%C2%A0%E2%82%AC275%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20the%20increase%2C%20European%20Commission%20President%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20stand%20by%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20in%20Gaza%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20region.%20Innocent%20Palestinians%20should%20not%20have%20to%20pay%20the%20price%20for%20the%20crimes%20of%20terrorist%20group%20Hamas.%20They%20face%20terrible%20conditions%20putting%20their%20lives%20at%20risk%20because%20of%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20sufficient%20food%20and%20other%20basic%20needs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EDeeply%20disturbed%20by%20images%20from%20Gaza.%20Every%20effort%20must%20be%20made%20to%20investigate%20what%20happened%20and%20ensure%20transparency%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHumanitarian%20aid%20is%20a%20lifeline%20for%20those%20in%20need%20and%20access%20to%20it%20must%20be%20ensured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20stand%20by%20civilians%2C%20urging%20their%20protection%20in%20line%20with%20international%20law%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%20(%40vonderleyen)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fvonderleyen%2Fstatus%2F1763504038262251792%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%201%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EU%20is%20the%20third-largest%20donor%20to%20UNRWA%20after%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Funited-states-of-america%2Ft-19065189%5C%22%3EUS%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20Germany.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20two%20leading%20donors%20also%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafter-us-germany-freeze-aid-to-unrwa-could-eu-follow%2Fa-68116182%5C%22%3Ehalted%20their%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20UNRWA%2C%20leaving%20the%20relief%20organisation%20with%20an%20uncertain%20future.%20Should%20the%20US%20and%20Germany%20continue%20to%20withhold%20payments%2C%20UNRWA%20could%20still%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fwill-unrwas-cash-crisis-lead-to-extremism-instability%2Fa-68309915%5C%22%3Eforced%20to%20suspend%20its%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20unified%20EU%20response%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bloc%E2%80%99s%2027%20member%20states%20are%20not%20united%20in%20their%20assessment%20of%20the%20situation%20in%20Gaza.%20While%20Germany%20has%20called%20the%20humanitarian%20situation%20%E2%80%9Cdisastrous%E2%80%9D%20and%20is%20looking%20to%20increase%20humanitarian%20assistance%20to%20people%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpalestinian-territories%2Ft-19099064%5C%22%3EPalestinian%20territories%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20has%20been%20reserved%20about%20criticising%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20actions.%20Berlin%20insists%20that%20Israel%20has%20the%20right%20to%20defend%20itself%2C%20and%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20operation%20against%20Hamas%20is%20necessary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20foreign%20minister%20Annalena%20Baerbock%20announced%20Germany%20was%20increasing%20humanitarian%20assistance%20for%20Gaza.%20She%20also%20joined%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20call%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20pause%E2%80%9D%20to%20ensure%20more%20aid%20could%20reach%20civilians%20and%20to%20secure%20the%20release%20of%20the%20remaining%20hostages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20EU%20member%20states%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspain%2Ft-18996264%5C%22%3ESpain%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Frepublic-of-ireland%2Ft-19249621%5C%22%3EIreland%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20been%20critical%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20campaign.%20In%20a%20joint%20letter%20to%20the%20European%20Commission%2C%20the%20countries%E2%80%99%C2%A0prime%20ministers%20demanded%20a%20review%20of%20the%20EU-Israel%20association%20agreement%20and%20asked%20the%20Commission%20to%20%E2%80%9Cact%20urgently%E2%80%9D%20to%20review%20whether%20Israel%20was%20complying%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fhuman-rights%2Ft-17455099%5C%22%3Ehuman%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20standards%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEric%20Mamer%2C%20a%20speaker%20for%20the%20European%20Commission%20in%20Brussels%2C%20said%20his%20office%20was%20looking%20into%20the%20request.%20The%20European%20Commission%20declined%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20incident%20where%20over%20100%20Palestinians%20were%20killed%20on%20Thursday%20as%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20reach%20an%20aid%20convoy.%20Gazan%20health%20officials%20reported%20scores%20of%20victims%20delivered%20to%20hospitals%20with%20gunshot%20wounds.%20Israeli%20officials%20said%20most%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20stampede.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVon%20der%20Leyen%20has%20called%20for%20an%20independent%20international%20investigation.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20cannot%20determine%20what%20has%20happened%2C%20we%20are%20not%20attributing%20blame%20or%20responsibility%2C%E2%80%9D%20her%20speaker%20said.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20to%20find%20out%20was%20has%20happened.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Feu-to-release-vital-funds-for-palestinian-aid-organization-unrwa%2Fa-68423061%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20translated%20from%20German%2C%20and%20was%20first%20published%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3EDW.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709378998000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F21131712%2F2620419248_a4fa7326fc_o-2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fafter-suspending-aid-money-over-israeli-allegations-eu-to-resume-payments-to-palestines-unrwa%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Europe