20is%20based%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98State%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Environment%202024%20report%E2%80%99%2C%20published%20by%20the%20think%20tank%20Centre%20for%20Science%20and%20Environment%20(CSE)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20data%20for%20which%20is%20drawn%20from%20the%20UN-backed%20Sustainable%20Development%20Report%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20India%20has%20improved%20its%20ranking%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20121st%20in%202022%20%E2%80%93%20it%20still%20trails%20countries%20like%20Bhutan%20(61st%2C%20the%20best%20in%20South%20Asia)%2C%20the%20Maldives%20(68th)%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20(83rd)%2C%20Nepal%20(99th)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(101st).%20Pakistan%20is%20at%20128th%20while%20Afghanistan%20is%20158th.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%20is%20behind%20many%20South%20Asian%20countries%20in%20(its%20performance%20towards)%20achieving%20its%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20that%20its%20economic%20process%20has%20not%20adequately%20rubbed%20off%20on%20the%20parameters%20linked%20to%20broad%20societal%20quality%20of%20life%20agendas%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20former%20UN%20undersecretary-general%20for%20economic%20and%20social%20affairs%2C%20Nitin%20Desai%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Findia-ranks-112th-on-progress-towards-un-mandated-sustainable-development-goals-in-2023%2Fcid%2F2004138%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20score%20of%2063.45%25%20in%202023%2C%20India%20marked%20a%20small%20improvement%20over%20the%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%2060.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20specific%20parameters%20of%20%E2%80%9Creducing%20inequalities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Clife%20on%20land%E2%80%9D%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20performance%20has%20deteriorated.%20Life%20on%20land%20relates%20to%20conserving%20biodiversity%2C%20where%20India%20is%20close%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20has%20also%20fared%20poorly%20on%20parameters%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20cities%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cequality%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cclean%20water%20and%20sanitation%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpeace%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20strong%20institutions%E2%80%9D.%20Its%20performance%20in%20relation%20to%20%E2%80%9Cno%20hunger%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20cities%20and%20communities%E2%80%9D%20has%20also%20stagnated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20its%20performance%20on%20%E2%80%9Cpoverty%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Csustainable%20consumption%E2%80%9D%20indicators%20appears%20to%20have%20remained%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20UN%20adopted%2017%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%20as%20a%20universal%20call%20to%20action%20to%20end%20poverty%20and%20protect%20the%20planet%2C%20and%20to%20ensure%20that%20by%202030%20everyone%20enjoys%20peace%20and%20prosperity.%20However%2C%20experts%20say%20the%202030%20deadline%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20met.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709367287000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F02133909%2FUntitled-design-23.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fun-sustainable-development-goals-india-ranked-112-among-166-countries-for-performance-in-2023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20trails%20countries%20like%20Bhutan%20(61st%2C%20the%20best%20in%20South%20Asia)%2C%20the%20Maldives%20(68th)%2C%20Sri%20Lanka%20(83rd)%2C%20Nepal%20(99th)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(101st).%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fun-sustainable-development-goals-india-ranked-112-among-166-countries-for-performance-in-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rihanna%20accidentally%20mispronounces%20Radhika%E2%80%99s%20name%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709367192000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.t