troops-ration-ammo-house-republicans-delay-aid%2Famp_articleshow%2F108156512.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Maoists%20claim%208th%20victim%3A%20Another%20BJP%20leader%20killed%20in%20Bastar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709360883000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108156495%2Cimgsize-39062.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fraipur%2Fmaoists-claim-eighth-victim-another-bjp-leader-killed-in-bastar%2Farticleshow%2F108156468.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20series%20of%20attacks%2C%20Maoists%20have%20targeted%20BJP%20leaders%20in%20Chhattisgarh's%20Bijapur%20district.%20Triupati%20Katla%20is%20the%20latest%20victim%2C%20succumbing%20to%20his%20injuries.%20This%20marks%20the%20eighth%20instance%20of%20a%20BJP%20leader%20falling%20victim%20to%20Maoist%20violence%20in%20the%20state%20since%20last%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22PARTHA%20SARATHI%20BEHERA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fraipur%2Fmaoists-claim-eighth-victim-another-bjp-leader-killed-in-bastar%2Farticleshow%2F108156468.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22GDP%20Growth%20Numbers%20Do%20Not%20Square%20with%20Consumption%20and%20Income%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F27093901%2F26172691320_ea02245a43_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20robust%208.4%25%20real%20GDP%20growth%20print%20for%20Q3%20contrasts%20the%20grim%20reality%20of%20household%20consumption%20and%20income%20situation.%20The%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fconsumption-expenditure-released-after-11-year-gap-highlights-persisting-inequality%5C%22%3Enational%20expenditure%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2022-23)%2C%20released%20after%20a%20lag%20of%2011%20years%20shows%20real%20consumption%20grew%20modestly%20at%203%25%20over%20the%20past%2011%20years%2C%20and%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20(PLFS)%C2%A0data%20indicates%20flat%20real%20incomes%20over%20the%20past%20four%20years.%20Also%2C%20most%20consumer%20companies%20have%20shown%20a%20lacklustre%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20not%20surprising%20is%20that%20the%20persisting%20discordance%20has%20accentuated%20in%20the%20Q3%20print%20and%20reflects%20in%20a)%20the%20large%20contribution%20of%20the%20discrepancy%20component%2C%20b)%20a%20sharp%20rise%20in%20net%20indirect%20taxes%20translating%20into%20enlarged%20expenditure%20GDP%2C%20and%20c)%20a%20disproportionate%20decline%20in%20imports%20relative%20to%20the%20decline%20in%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImportantly%2C%20the%20latest%20projection%20of%20nominal%20GDP%20for%20FY24%20at%20INR%20293.9%20trillion%20is%20a%20decline%20of%202.6%25%20from%20the%20FY24%20budget%20projection%20and%20-0.9%25%20over%20the%20first%20advance%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20headlines%2C%20the%20Q3FY24%20GDP%20at%208.4%25%20Year-on-Year%20came%20in%20higher%20than%20the%20Central%20Statistics%20Office%E2%80%99s%20projection%20thereby%20prompting%20an%20upward%20revision%20in%20the%20second%20advance%20estimates%20(AE)%20for%20the%20full%20year%20FY24%20at%207.6%25%20YoY%20vs%20the%201st%20AE%20of%207.3%25%20YoY%20(Jan%E2%80%9924).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20a%20seasonally%20adjusted%20(sa)%20basis%20the%20real%20GDP%20rose%20modestly%20at%200.8%25%20QoQ%2C%20implying%20an%20annualised%20growth%20of%203.1%25.%20Putting%20together%2C%20the%20average%20QoQ%20rise%20during%20Q1-Q3%20FY24%20at%201.7%25%20translates%20into%20an%20annualised%20growth%20of%204.1%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECore%20GDP%20(GDP%20ex%20discrepancy%20or%20the%20unaccounted%20portion)%20grew%20by%204.7%25%20YoY%2C%20or%20just%2055%25%20of%20the%20headline%20GDP%20growth.%20Also%2C%20along%20with%20the%200.9%25%20QoQ%20sa%20in%20Q3%2C%20the%20annualised%20Q1-Q3%20FY24%20growth%20in%20core%20GDP%20is%20averaging%20at%20just%203.2%25.%20Thus%2C%20notwithstanding%20the%20strong%20headline%20print%2C%20the%20growth%20momentum%20is%20fading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20details%20of%20the%20expenditure%20side%20bare%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20supposedly%20strong%20growth%20is%20primarily%20coming%20from%20a%20sharp%20contraction%20in%20imports%2C%20thereby%20resulting%20in%20a%20disproportionate%20decline%20in%20external%20deficit%2C%20thereby%20reducing%20the%20drag%20on%20the%20GDP%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20an%20annualised%20basis%2C%20imports%20contracted%20by%2022%25%20in%20Q3%2C%20whereas%20exports%20expanded%20modestly%20by%200.9%25.%20The%20declining%20imports%20are%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20contraction%20in%20domestic%20demand.%20Overall%20consumption%2C%20comprising%20private%20(-0.7%20QoQ%20sa)%20and%20government%20(-7.9%25%20QoQ%20sa)%2C%20contracted%20by%201.8%25%20QoQ%20sa%2C%20annualising%20into%20a%207%25%20contraction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20growth%20in%20real%20exports%20(0.9%25%20sa%20annualised)%20indicates%20that%20despite%20the%20slowdown%2C%20global%20demand%20conditions%20are%20still%20better%20than%20domestic%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowth%20in%20gross%20capital%20formation%20has%20decelerated%20to%2010.6%25%20from%2011.6%25%20in%202QFY24.%20But%20it%20remained%20flat%20sequentially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20output%20side%2C%20real%20GVA%20growth%20witnessed%20a%20marked%20deceleration%20from%208.2%25%20YoY%20in%20Q1%20FY24%20to%206.5%25%20YoY%20in%20Q3%20FY24.%20Sequentially%2C%20it%20grew%20by%20only%200.1%25%20QoQ%20sa%20and%20remained%20flat%20since%20the%20last%20two%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgriculture%20GVA%20contracted%20by%200.8%25%20YoY%20in%20Q3%20FY24%20with%20a%20sequential%20average%20decline%20of%200.6%25%20QoQ%20sustaining%20for%20three%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndustry%20decelerated%20to%2010.4%25%20YoY%2C%20also%20showed%20signs%20of%20sequential%20slowdown%20as%20it%20contracted%20by%200.3%25%20QoQ%20sa%20with%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20contracting%20by%200.5%25%20QoQ%20sa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20services%20sector%20expanded%20by%207%25%20YoY%20and%201%25%20QoQ%20sa%20as%20the%20trade%20and%20financial%20services%20expanded%20sequentially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20contrasting%20rise%20in%20real%20GDP%20growth%20and%20a%20sharp%20deceleration%20in%20real%20GVA%20growth%20marks%20the%20substantial%20rise%20in%20the%20incidence%20of%20net%20indirect%20taxes%20on%20the%20expenditure%20side%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENet%20indirect%20tax%2FGVA%20at%209.7%25%20in%20Q3%20was%20sharply%20higher%20than%207.8%25%20a%20year%20ago%20and%208.9%25%20in%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20In%20absolute%20terms%2C%20net%20indirect%20taxes%20grew%20by%2032%25%20YoY%20and%2012.6%25%20QoQ.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20the%20elevated%20net%20indirect%20taxes%20continue%20to%20impinge%20on%20the%20overall%20domestic%20demand%2C%20which%20is%20already%20being%20dragged%20down%20by%20the%20decline%20in%20real%20household%20incomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20on%20the%20face%20of%20it%2C%20though%20the%20headline%20GDP%20growth%20looks%20robust%2C%20it%20camouflages%20the%20contraction%20in%20domestic%20consumption%20demand.%20It%20is%20thus%20reasonable%20to%20assume%20that%20private%20capex%20would%20have%20remained%20languid%2C%20thereby%20signifying%20the%20continued%20overreliance%20on%20government%20capex.%20The%20statistical%20boost%20from%20the%20enlarged%20discrepancy%20component%20has%20meant%20that%20the%20core%20growth%20is%20trending%20much%20lower%20at%204%25%20over%20the%20past%20six%20quarters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sustainability%20of%20even%20the%20core%20growth%20is%20suspect%20as%20the%20interim%20budget%20FY25%20has%20scaled%20down%20the%20growth%20in%20infra%20sector%20allocation%20(roads%2C%20railways%2C%20and%20defence%20to%205.2%25)%20and%20fragile%20support%20from%20the%20disproportionate%20contraction%20in%20imports%20relative%20to%2