s%2F1763331544045994157%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Einternational%20humanitarian%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20region%2C%20there%20was%20strong%20condemnation%20from%20Saudi%20Arabia%20to%20Kuwait%20and%20Qatar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2024%2F02%2F29%2Fpolitics%2Fbiden-gaza-incidents-ceasefire-talks%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ecompeting%20versions%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20incident%20and%20warned%20that%20the%20deaths%20would%20complicate%20the%20negotiations%20for%20release%20of%20hostages%20and%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20urgent%20meeting%20held%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20discussed%20Thursday%E2%80%99s%20killings%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Palestinian%20ambassador%20to%20the%20UN%2C%20Riyad%20Mansour%2C%20the%20US%20blocked%20the%20issuing%20of%20a%20statement%20by%20the%20Council%2C%20arguing%20that%20there%20were%20contradictory%20reports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20intensity%20of%20the%20international%20outcry%20meant%20that%20India%20did%20not%20have%20much%20choice%20but%20to%20issue%20a%20condemnatory%20statement%2C%20even%20though%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20name%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20deaths%20or%20cite%20Israel%20by%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20October%207%20attack%20by%20Hamas%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20had%20simply%20tweeted%20that%20India%20was%20in%20%E2%80%9Csolidarity%E2%80%9D%20with%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20explosion%20in%20a%20Gaza%20hospital%20killed%20hundreds%20two%20weeks%20later%2C%20the%20Indian%20PM%20for%20the%20first%20time%20during%20this%20current%20conflict%20reiterated%20that%20New%20Delhi%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmodi-palestine-authority-president-mahmoud-abbas-call-israel-gaza%5C%22%3Etraditionally%20supported%3C%