siness--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fministry-of-defence-makes-indigenous-purchases-of-over-rs-39-000-crore-124030101026_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fministry-of-defence-makes-indigenous-purchases-of-over-rs-39-000-crore-124030101026_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Drowning%20Jewel%3A%20Tapestry%20of%20Dal%20Lake's%20Decline%20and%20Fishing%20Community's%20Struggle%20in%20Kashmir%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185358%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.53.13-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20picturesque%20landscapes%20of%20Dal%20Lake%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20a%20small%20community%20silently%20grapples%20with%20the%20intricate%20interplay%20of%20environmental%20degradation%2C%20urbanisation%20and%20the%20changing%20nature%20of%20their%20relationship%20with%20their%20ancestral%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnthropogenic%20(human-induced)%20environmental%20degradation%20has%20been%20on%20the%20agenda%20of%20humanity%20for%20a%20long%20time%20now%2C%20however%2C%20even%20the%20most%20beautiful%20and%20popular%20tourist%20destinations%20%E2%80%93%20which%20one%20might%20assume%20are%20the%20most%20protected%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20world%20seem%20to%20be%20choking%20by%20the%20surge%20of%20plastic%20and%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20named%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsrinagar.nic.in%2Ftourist-place%2Fdal-lake%2F%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CJewel%20in%20the%20crown%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20state%2C%20is%20drowning%20in%20municipal%20sewage%2C%20and%20pollution%2C%20covered%20with%20weeds%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fgallery%2F2021%2F9%2F23%2Fkashmir-dal-lake-weeds-sewage-environment-pollution%5C%22%3Epatches%20of%20garbage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%C2%A0people%20(those%20living%20in%20houseboats)%20bear%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20urbanisation.%20Thanks%20to%20the%20rapid%20commercialisation%20of%20the%20surrounding%20region%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20just%20paying%20through%20their%20wages%20and%20house%2C%20but%20also%20through%20their%20self.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20unravelling%20causes%20of%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20pollution%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Dal%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20fish.%20But%20this%20sewage%20has%20destroyed%20the%20fish.%20All%20the%20garbage%20goes%20into%20the%20Dal.%20We%20used%20to%20drink%20this%20water%2C%20but%20today%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20wash%20your%20face%20with%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Javed%20Ahmed%2C%20a%20fisherman%20who%20was%20relocated%20to%20the%20fisherman%20colony%20in%20Habbak%2C%20an%20area%20%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20vicinity%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20of%20sewage%20and%20pollution%20in%20the%20Dal%20has%20been%20a%20well-documented%20phenomenon%20for%20a%20few%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2020%2F03%2F02%2F70-of-srinagars-sewerage-goes-into-dal-lake-experts%2F%5C%22%3E%20years%20now%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcademic%20and%20scientific%20work%20has%20been%20uncovering%20the%20causes%20of%20pollution%20and%20its%20permanent%20impacts.%20Noteworthy%20transformations%20occurred%20in%20the%20land%20use%20and%20land%20cover%20(LULC)%20within%20the%20lake%20between%201859%20and%202013%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20surrounding%20areas%20from%201962%20to%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.limno.2016.11.008%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20the%20demographic%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicates%20that%20the%20human%20population%20within%20the%20lake%20has%20surpassed%20double%20the%20national%20growth%20rate.%20These%20changes%20in%20both%20LULC%20and%20demographics%20have%20had%20adverse%20effects%20on%20the%20pollution%20status%20of%20the%20previously%20pristine%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Javed%20blames%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fwork-underway-in-srinagar-under-various-smart-city-projects-officials-123091200298_1.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20smart%20city%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20in%202019%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20influx%20of%20tourism%20which%20choked%20their%20spaces%20%E2%80%93%20the%20sewage%20has%20been%20polluting%20Dal%20for%20a%20long%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20region%E2%80%99s%20accelerated%20development%20has%20led%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20the%20fishing%20trade%20and%20displacement%20of%20people%20from%20their%20ancestral%20properties.%20This%20change%20is%20fuelled%20by%20the%20constant%20need%20for%20beautification%20of%20places%20like%20the%20Boulevard%20and%20the%20foreshore%20road-%20in%20which%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20simply%20do%20not%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20widening%20of%20the%20foreshore%20road%20along%20the%20Dal%2C%20under%20the%20Smart%20City%20Project%2C%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20members%20of%20Hanji%20community%20to%20put%20stalls%20of%20barbeque%20or%20selling%20of%20vegetables%20on%20roadside%20This%20has%20disrupted%20the%20livelihoods%20and%20ancestral%20fishing%20practices%20of%20many%20among%20the%20Hanji%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20filed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fenvironment-and-nature-india-lakes-kashmir-278cedc58a77adce627505452ca2f9a4%5C%22%3ETariq%20Ahmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20(a%20houseboat%20owner)%20in%202017%2C%20%E2%80%9CForty-four%20million%20litres%20(11%20million%20gallons)%20of%20sewage%20was%20released%20into%20the%20lake%20from%20the%20city%20each%20day.%20In%20addition%2C%20about%201%20million%20litres%20(260%2C000%20gallons)%20of%20sewage%20came%20from%20houseboats.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dominant%20narrative%20has%20been%20that%20the%20houseboats%20pollute%20the%20Dal%2C%20however%2C%20the%20findings%20showcase%20otherwise.%20The%20photographs%20taken%20by%20environmentalists%20and%20journalists%20highlight%20the%20extent%20of%20eutrophication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22843%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM.png%20843w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01141509%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-2.14.23-PM-300x215.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699604%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22604%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPhoto%3A%20Land%20use%20land%20cover%20within%20the%20Dal%20lake%20from%201859%20to%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20present%20condition%20of%20the%20Dal%20is%20the%20result%20of%20a%20complex%20mesh%20of%20activities%20happening%20throughout%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20as%20the%20surge%20of%20residents%20and%20tourists%20has%20grown%20exponentially.%20The%20findings%20from%20the%20interviews%20of%20Hanji%20people%20are%20in%20congruence%20with%20what%20the%20research%20and%20the%20local%20reporting%20have%20been%20suggesting%20that%20sewage%20dumping%2C%20population%20rise%20and%20mismanagement%20is%20causing%20irreversible%20damage%20to%20the%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20beautification%20of%20Dal%20is%20thriving%20%E2%80%93%20with%20proper%20roads%2C%20footpaths%2C%20and%20new%20shops%20opening%20to%20cater%20to%20the%20growing%20population%20of%20tourists%20%E2%80%93%20the%20lake%20itself%20is%20slowly%20dying%2C%20and%20with%20that%2C%20the%20Hanji%20community%20is%20also%20slowly%20being%20removed%20from%20their%20ancestral%20fishing%20grounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoss%20of%20biodiversity%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMapping%20the%20impacts%20of%20the%20pollution%20happening%20at%20Dal%20is%20a%20mammoth%20effort%20which%20scientists%20have%20been%20carrying%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20have%20been%20experiencing%20these%20impacts%20even%20before%20the%20issue%20became%20mainstream.%20Fishermen%20who%20have%20been%20living%20inside%20the%20Dal%20for%20decades%20have%20mentioned%20how%20the%20fish%20count%20in%20Dal%20has%20gone%20down%20exponentially%2C%20and%20the%20native%20species%20have%20almost%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FlhcIWXttOO8%3Fsi%3DjLDBCKZmyOdO2GE1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20old%20fisherman%20who%20has%20been%20living%20in%20the%20Dal%20for%20decades%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20fish%20in%20the%20Dal%20are%20small.%20Because%20of%20the%20sewage%2C%20the%20fish%20have%20declined.%20This%20sewage%20affects%20the%20seeds%20of%20the%20fish.%20We%20used%20to%20cultivate%20lotus%20stem%20(Nadru)%20but%20that%20is%20also%20declining%20now%20%5BThe%20LCMA%20is%20using%20machines%20to%20clear%20the%20nadru%20growth%20in%20the%20Dal%5D.%20The%20floods%20had%20a%20devastating%20effect%20on%20the%20fish.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAzmat%2C%20another%20fisherman%20working%20in%20the%20Tailbal%20region%20of%20the%20lake%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20fish%20here%20used%20to%20be%20plenty%2C%20but%20now%20they%E2%80%99ve%20depleted%20significantly.%20We%20are%20left%20with%20little%20to%20no%20work.%20We%20face%20a%20lot%20of%20hardships%20because%20of%20this.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20people%20used%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20which%20included%20various%20flora%20and%20fauna%2C%20which%20were%20also%20part%20of%20their%20diet.%20The%20eutrophication%20of%20the%20lake%20paired%20with%20reduced%20water%20quality%20has%20made%20the%20water%20unfit%20for%20anything%2C%20while%20the%20local%20authorities%20had%20installed%20Sewage%20Treatment%20Plants%20(STPs)%20to%20mitigate%20the%20inflow%20of%20toxic%20sewage%2C%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2020%2F03%2F02%2F70-of-srinagars-sewerage-goes-into-dal-lake-experts%2F%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20their%20tragic%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20been%20reported%20that%20about%2070%25%20of%20the%20sewage%20generated%20in%20Srinagar%20City%20finds%20its%20way%20into%20the%20Lake.%20Three%20STPs%20are%20functioning%20under%20the%20control%20of%20LAWDA.%20These%20are%20heavily%20over-utilised%20and%20under-maintained%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Fkashmir%2Ftechnical-expert-committee-to-determine-buffers-around-dal-allied-water-bodies%2F%5C%22%3Ecommittee%20of%20experts%20(CoE)%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20appointed%20by%20the%20High%20Court%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%20said%20in%20its%20latest%20report%2C%20according%20to%20GNS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20STPs%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20renovated%20soon%2C%20however%2C%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkashmirobserver.net%2F2023%2F10%2F03%2Fdal-lake-loses-sheen-to-red-algae-bloom%2F%5C%22%3ERed%20Algae%20bloom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20dubbed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20phenomenon%E2%80%9D%20by%20government%20officials%2C%20seems%20to%20show%20no%20sign%20of%20change%20after%20two%20years%20of%20said%20%E2%80%98renovation%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20carried%20by%20a%20daily%20newspaper%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.greaterkashmir.com%2Ftodays-paper%2Fsrinagar-city%2Frs-239-crore-spent-on-dal-lake-conservation-in-last-5-yrs-goi%2F%5C%22%3EGreater%20Kashmir%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20March%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20had%20spent%20Rs%20759%20crore%20for%20cleaning%20of%20the%20Dal%20from%202002%20to%202018%20and%20the%20UT%20administration%20has%20spent%20Rs%20239%20crores%20from%202019-2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20spending%20so%20much%20on%20the%20cleaning%20of%20the%20Dal%2C%20the%20Hanjis%20do%20not%20see%20themselves%20as%20the%20part%20of%20the%20process%20except%20that%20they%20are%20employed%20by%20the%20LCMA%20department%20occasionally%20to%20manually%20clean%20the%20Dal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20have%20been%20beneficial%20if%20the%20government%20would%20have%20taken%20into%20consideration%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20elder%20generation%20of%20the%20fishing%20community%20living%20in%20the%20Dal%20by%20involving%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomic%20impacts%20of%20environmental%20degradation%20and%20urbanisation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disappearing%20flora%20and%20fauna%20do%20not%20just%20create%20shifts%20in%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20but%20they%20also%20impact%20those%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20the%20ecosystem%20itself%20for%20their%20livelihoods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20destruction%20of%20fish%20has%20been%20devastating%20for%20the%20Hanji%20people%20economically.%20It%20is%20impacting%20their%20business%20and%20leading%20many%20of%20them%20towards%20losses%20and%20throwing%20them%20deeper%20into%20poverty.%C2%A0Since%20the%20Hanji%20community%20is%20a%20fishing%20community%2C%20their%20main%20source%20of%20income%20is%20selling%20fish%20and%20vegetables%20which%20grow%20out%20of%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FxxYLkVUMJNk%3Fsi%3DAB-vh2NBzzW-PZxx%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20explained%20by%20Azmat%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20inflation%20has%20risen.%20Prices%20of%20commodities%20keep%20rising.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20earn%20that%20much.%20We%20have%20to%20buy%20fish%20from%20outside%2C%20and%20if%20it%20gets%20spoilt%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20on%20us.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20Azmat%20talks%20about%20here%20is%20a%20real%20problem%20which%20is%20becoming%20commonplace.%20The%20ecosystem%20of%20the%20lake%20is%20destroyed%2C%20wherein%20no%20cultivation%20of%20any%20flora%2C%20or%20no%20breeding%20of%20any%20fish%20through%20seeds%20is%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20pushing%20Hanji%20people%20to%20buy%20fish%20from%20fish%20farms%20and%20other%20states%20and%20sell%20it%20at%20a%20loss.%20This%20economic%20loss%20is%20putting%20immense%20pressure%20on%20their%20livelihoods%20and%20causing%20them%20to%20move%20away%20from%20the%20field%20of%20work%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20issues%20are%20also%20exacerbated%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20support%20from%20the%20local%20authorities%20and%20the%20government.%20While%20only%20one%20interviewee%20mentioned%20that%20businesses%20were%20hit%20post%20Article%20370%20implementation%2C%20the%20criticism%20of%20the%20government%20bodies%20was%20a%20recurring%20theme%20in%20the%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20people%20possess%20a%20fear%20of%20officials%20and%20hence%20were%20paranoid%20of%20researchers%20asking%20any%20questions%2C%20including%20on%20their%20daily%20lives%20or%20livelihoods.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20police%20come%20and%20destroy%20our%20fishes%2C%20throw%20them%20in%20water.%20In%20Lal%20Chowk%2C%20police%20throw%20them%20in%20Jhelum%20and%20we%20face%20loses%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ghulam%20Nabi%2C%20a%2052-year-old%20fisherman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20major%20issue%20which%20almost%20all%20the%20interviewees%20talked%20about%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20proper%20market%20to%20sell%20their%20produce.%20Many%20of%20them%20sit%20on%20the%20foothpath%20near%20the%20road%20and%20sell%20fish%2C%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20told%20to%20move%20frequently%20because%20they%20disturb%20the%20%E2%80%98aesthetic%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20newly%20constructed%20roads.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJana%2C%20a%2060-year-old%20woman%20who%20sells%20fish%20near%20the%20Dargah%20Hazratbal%20said%20that%20she%20has%20to%20pay%20rent%20to%20sit%20on%20the%20road%20and%20set%20up%20her%20stall%2C%20and%20the%20biggest%20problem%20she%20faces%20is%20the%20constant%20relocation%20to%20new%20locations%20as%20she%20has%20to%20carry%20all%20her%20belongings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGhulam%20Mohammad%2C%20who%20sells%20fish%20on%20the%20foreshore%20road%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20municipality%2C%20they%20take%20all%20our%20stuff.%20I%20have%20kept%20my%20shikara%20%5Bboat%5D%20here%2C%20I%20put%20all%20my%20stuff%20in%20that%20and%20leave.%20They%20even%20take%20tubs%20with%20fish%20in%20it.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20used%20to%20sell%20fish%20on%20the%20other%20side%20but%20after%20they%20made%20the%20pathway%20along%20the%20road%20they%20had%20to%20shift.%20Our%20trade%20is%20based%20on%20water%2C%20we%20had%20asked%20them%20to%20at%20least%20make%20a%20stairwell%20along%20the%20road%20so%20that%20we%20may%20get%20some%20water%2C%20but%20they%20did%20not.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20subjugation%20from%20authorities%20puts%20immense%20pressure%20on%20the%20people%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%20because%20most%20of%20them%20are%20struggling%20already%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20as%20the%20sales%20of%20fish%20are%20almost%20always%20in%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20authorities%20seem%20to%20believe%20that%20removing%20Hanji%20people%20from%20the%20area%20and%20relocating%20them%20to%20a%20new%20location%20will%20somehow%20improve%20the%20condition%20of%20the%20lake%20itself%2C%20but%20even%20after%20multiple%20attempts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thekashmirmonitor.net%2Fsave-dal-lake-sdrf-lwda-launch-major-drive-to-restore-glory-of-world-famous-water-body%2F%5C%22%3Ethe%20issue%20remains%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidering%20the%20huge%20sums%20being%20spent%20on%20the%20Save%20Dal%20Project%2C%20clearly%2C%20there%20is%20a%20deeper%20issue%20that%20the%20authorities%20are%20failing%20to%20understand%2C%20and%20the%20findings%20showcase%20how%20they%20might%20have%20been%20pushing%20away%20the%20solution%20all%20this%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERole%20of%20the%20Hanji%20people%20in%20maintaining%20the%20ecosystem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20government%20wants%20to%20beautify%20the%20Dal%2C%20so%20they%20relocated%20us%20but%20they%20are%20not%20able%20to%20keep%20it%20clean.%20We%20used%20to%20keep%20it%20clean%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Azmat%2C%20who%20emphasises%20on%20the%20role%20of%20the%20community%20in%20maintaining%20the%20Dal%20as%20well%20as%20keeping%20it%20in%20an%20equilibrium.%20The%20overall%20process%20of%20urbanisation%20and%20removal%20of%20Hanji%20people%20has%20led%20to%20significant%20changes%20in%20the%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20might%20be%20removing%20the%20Hanji%20people%20from%20the%20areas%20for%20%E2%80%98aesthetic%E2%80%99%20reasons%2C%20it%20is%20having%20a%20counter%20effect%20because%20the%20lake%E2%80%99s%20condition%20was%20also%20a%20result%20of%20the%20care%20and%20practice%20which%20went%20into%20maintaining%20such%20a%20fragile%20ecosystem.%20The%20Hanji%20people%20had%20been%20a%20big%20part%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20the%20prevalent%20use%20of%20%3Cem%3Elamba%20zaal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20longer%20nets%2C%20which%20kill%20the%20seed-laying%20fish%2C%20and%20stop%20the%20fishes%20from%20procreating.%20The%20Hanji%20people%20used%20the%20%3Cem%3Egoal%20zaal%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20the%20round%20net%2C%20which%20requires%20skill%20to%20use%3B%20the%20entry%20of%20non-Hanji%20fishermen%20and%20the%20use%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Elamba%20zaal%20%3C%2Fem%3Eby%20them%20has%20been%20reducing%20the%20fish%20count%20further%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20people%2C%20then%2C%20seem%20to%20be%20eager%20to%20help%20maintain%20the%20lake%20but%20have%20been%20denied%20any%20chance%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20person%20asserted%20that%20the%20trade%20would%20have%20been%20different%20had%20there%20been%20a%20Mahigir%20person%20(fisherman)%20in%20the%20fisheries%20department%2C%20he%20adds%2C%E2%80%9CA%20Mahigir%20knows%20these%20waters%20by%20heart.%20He%20knows%20how%20to%20keep%20this%20clean.%20How%20to%20catch%20fish.%20How%20to%20use%20the%20net.%20Thus%2C%20they%20would%20have%20prevented%20the%20illegal%20fishing%20activities%20in%20the%20lake.%20The%20net%20destroys%20the%20seed.%20It%20has%20been%20banned.%20The%20Mahigir%20has%20the%20know-how%20of%20the%20lake.%20At%20least%2C%20they%20would%20have%20provided%20the%20information%20to%20the%20concerned%20depts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20idea%20which%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fao.org%2F3%2Fw2352e%2FW2352E06.htm%5C%22%3EParticipatory%20Rural%20Appraisal%20(PRA)%3C%2Fa%3E%20framework%20employed%20in%20environmental%20projects%2C%20wherein%20the%20rural%20population%20is%20involved%20in%20the%20various%20processes%20of%20the%20project%2C%20so%20as%20to%20ensure%20true%20value%20to%20the%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20apparent%20lack%20of%20representation%20of%20Hanji%20people%20in%20the%20decision-making%20mechanism%20which%20leads%20to%20such%20watered-down%20efforts%20to%20help%20the%20community.%20The%20official%20engineer%20of%20the%20LCMA%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Dal%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20LCMA%20but%20unfortunately%20we%20have%20other%20departments%20interfering%20in%20our%20work.%20For%20example%2C%20we%20have%20been%20tasked%20to%20clean%20the%20Dal%2C%20now%20fisheries%20department%20has%20provided%20the%20license%20for%20cultivating%20%3Cem%3Enadru%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20we%20tried%20to%20remove%20that%20but%20due%20to%20media%20highlights%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t.%20All%20the%20departments%20do%20as%20they%20wish.%20That%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20sorry%20state%20of%20the%20Dal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20clearly%20shows%20the%20lack%20of%20coherence%20and%20clarity%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20organising%20a%20systematic%20approach%20towards%20reformation%20of%20the%20Dal%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20hearing%20the%20people.%20These%20internal%20inefficiencies%20make%20apparent%20the%20need%20of%20a%20PRA-like%20framework%2C%20wherein%20the%20grassroots%20governance%20model%20can%20create%20a%20better%20way%20of%20handling%20sensitive%20ecosystems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20physical%20and%20social%20erasure%20of%20identity%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20the%20Hanji%20people%20have%20been%20removed%20from%20their%20homes%2C%20their%20ancestral%20livelihoods%20have%20been%20destroyed%2C%20and%20their%20trade%20has%20changed%20so%20drastically%20that%20not%20many%20of%20them%20would%20want%20their%20children%20to%20continue%20the%20trade.%20This%20kind%20of%20impact%20is%20not%20just%20the%20result%20of%20environmental%20issues%2C%20it%20is%20a%20result%20of%20a%20systemic%20subjugation%20of%20a%20particular%20community%20amid%20a%20blind%20race%20for%20development%20and%20growth%20to%20fulfil%20the%20needs%20of%20one%20section%20of%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20community%20has%20already%20been%20relocated%20to%20different%20regions%20which%20has%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20carry%20out%20their%20activities%20as%20usual.%20With%20this%20displacement%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20just%20losing%20money%2C%20but%20also%20a%20longstanding%20part%20of%20their%20identity%20and%20belongingness%2C%20which%20is%20fuelled%20by%20a%20misrepresentation%20of%20their%20role%20in%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20lake%20and%20its%20%E2%80%98pollution%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20development%20is%20tainted%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20marginalisation%2C%20there%20is%20a%20visible%20difference%20in%20the%20house%20of%20the%20Hanji%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%20%3C%2Fem%3E(locality)%C2%A0and%20non-Hanji%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20if%20one%20utilises%20a%20spatial%20lens%2C%20it%20becomes%20apparent%20how%20the%20spatiality%20of%20development%20plays%20a%20big%20part%20in%20erasing%20the%20identity%20of%20these%20communities%20which%20have%20been%20part%20of%20this%20space%20even%20longer%20than%20most%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20understood%20that%20fishing%20is%20not%20only%20the%20livelihood%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%2C%20it%20is%20also%20a%20part%20of%20their%20culture.%20So%2C%20the%20displacement%20of%20the%20members%20of%20this%20community%20means%20denial%20of%20cultural%20identity%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0The%20cultural%20ramifications%20of%20rapid%20urbanisation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20halcyon%20days%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake%20are%20slowly%20losing%20their%20charm%2C%20as%20the%20lake%20and%20its%20ancestral%20custodians%20of%20the%20Hanji%20community%20grapple%20with%20the%20repercussions%20of%20climate%20change%20amidst%20rapid%20urbanisation.%20Scientific%20findings%20and%20local%20narratives%20uncover%20the%20complex%20web%20of%20forces%20which%20has%20caused%20the%20decline%20of%20this%20once-pristine%20lake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20599px)%2085vw%2C%20599px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22599%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM.png%20599w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185556%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.55.05-PM-300x224.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-699695%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22448%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EWeeds%20and%20algae%20growth%20on%20the%20interiors%20of%20the%20Dal%20Lake.%C2%A0Photo%3A%20Najam%20Us%20Saqib%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hanji%20community%20and%20their%20traditional%20way%20of%20life%20are%20being%20impacted%20immensely%20as%20the%20unrelenting%20degradation%20of%20the%20lake%20continues%20despite%20the%20efforts%20by%20the%20state.%20The%20removal%20of%20the%20Hanji%20people%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20beautification%20efforts%20is%20shortsighted%20and%20overlooks%20their%20valuable%20traditional%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20erosion%20of%20their%20identity%20is%20a%20consequence%20which%20might%20be%20the%20most%20irreversible%20and%20tragic%20of%20all%20the%20losses.%20This%20process%20is%20emblematic%20of%20the%20larger%20problem%20we%20face%20when%20balancing%20rapid%20growth%20and%20change%20in%20society.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20the%20inherent%20link%20between%20the%20Hanji%20people%2C%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20and%20sustainable%20development%20is%20vital.%20It%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20inclusivity%2C%20community%20engagement%2C%20and%20preserving%20cultural%20identities%20to%20secure%20a%20harmonious%20and%20resilient%20future%20for%20this%20jewel%20in%20the%20crown%20of%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAcknowledgment%20Note%3A%20The%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fvisualstoryboardscnes.in%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EVisual%20Storyboard%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.jgu.edu.in%2Fjslh%2Fresearch-centres%2Fcentre-for-new-economics-studies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eteam%20of%20CNES%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20would%20like%20to%20thank%20Dr.%20Khalid%20Wasim%20Hassan%20for%20his%20guidance%20with%20the%20fieldwork%20of%20the%20study.%20We%20also%20thank%20Ms.%20Maria%20Shawl%2C%20Mr.%20Zahid%20Sultan%2C%20and%20Ms.%20Bismah%20Yousuf%20for%20their%20help%20during%20the%20field%20work.%20Video%20essays%20from%20this%20field%20story%20are%20accessible%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutube.com%2Fplaylist%3Flist%3DPL8RbNXSvnr8Swc2c8BsmjH16QMVL--Ja6%26si%3DuEA9tc-JQpZU-w0C%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20Dean%2C%20Office%20of%20Interdisciplinary%20Studies%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.jgu.edu.in%2Fjslh%2Fresearch-centres%2Fcentre-for-new-economics-studies%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECNES%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20with%20Saw%20Swee%20Hock%20Southeast%20Asia%20Centre%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%20an%20Honorary%20Research%20Fellow%20with%20Birkbeck%20College%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20Najam%20Us%20Saqib%20is%20a%20PhD%20Student%20and%20a%20Research%20Analyst%20with%20CNES%20Visual%20Storyboard%20Team.%20Ishfaq%20Wani%20is%20a%20PhD%20Student%20and%20a%20Research%20Analyst%20with%20CNES%20Visual%20Storyboard%20Team.%20Jayendra%20Singh%20is%20a%20Masters%20Student%20and%20a%20Research%20Assistant%20with%20CNES.%20Hima%20Trisha%20is%20a%20Law%20Student%20and%20a%20Senior%20Research%20Assistant%20with%20CNES.%20Video%20editing%20credits%20belong%20to%20Mr.%20Rajan%20Mishra.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709310563000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F01185358%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-01-at-6.53.13-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-drowning-jewel-tapestry-of-dal-lakes-decline-and-fishing-communitys-struggle-in-kashmir%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Acknowledging%20the%20inherent%20link%20between%20the%20Hanji%20people%2C%20Dal%20Lake%2C%20and%20sustainable%20development%20is%20vital.%20It%20emphasises%20the%20importance%20of%20inclusivity%2C%20community%20engagement%2C%20and%20preserving%20cultural%20identities%20to%20secure%20a%20harmonious%20and%20resilient%20future.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-drowning-jewel-tapestry-of-dal-lakes-decline-and-fishing-communitys-struggle-in-kashmir%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Uttrakhand's%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20Is%20a%20Mere%20Extension%20of%20Highly%20Controlled%20Lives%20Indian%20Women%20Lead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18112019%2FFEE464CC-1368-48CB-AF2D-1EA659E84547.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20provocation%20being%20offered%20by%20the%20recent%20Uniform%20Civil%20Code%20(UCC)%20legislation%2C%20passed%20in%20Uttarakhand%20on%20February%207%2C%202024%2C%20on%20the%20penal%20requirement%20to%20register%20live-in%20heterosexual%20relationships%2C%20needs%20a%20matching%20and%20appropriately%20hard-hitting%20response.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20it%20stands%2C%20right-wing%20conservatives%20find%20it%20easy%20to%20dismiss%20constitutional%20arguments%20that%20permit%20consenting%20adults%20to%20be%20in%20a%20relationship%20without%20interference%20from%20the%20state%20or%20caste%20and%20community%2C%20as%20middle%20class%2C%20%E2%80%98woke%E2%80%99%20and%20out%20of%20touch%20with%20the%20real%20India%20or%20Bharat%20as%20they%20prefer%20to%20call%20it%20today.%20To%20my%20mind%2C%20both%20positions%20are%20problematic.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criticism%20that%20the%20compulsory%20registration%20process%2C%20six%20months%20into%20or%20out%20of%20a%20partnership%2C%20infringes%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20illegitimately%20criminalises%20and%20infantilises%20adult%20relations%2C%20does%20not%20go%20far%20enough.%20Divested%20of%20all%20culpability%2C%20the%20underlying%20cultural%20presumptions%20of%20the%20regulation%20have%20not%20come%20up%20for%20public%20discussion%20at%20all.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20live-in%20relationship%20in%20India%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20very%20clear%2C%20rides%20on%20the%20back%20of%20the%20moral%20and%20statistical%20norm%20of%20heterosexual%20marriage%2C%20obligatorily%20%E2%80%9Carranged%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eeven%20by%20oneself%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewith%20the%20%E2%80%98correct%E2%80%99%20person%20of%20the%20opposite%20sex.%20The%20parental%20and%20community%20surveillance%20the%20UCC%20authorises%20for%20the%20live-in%20relationship%20is%20not%20very%20different%20from%20that%20already%20in%20place%20for%20the%20Indian%20arranged%20marriage.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPenal%20intrusion%20into%20the%20bedrooms%20of%20adult%20persons%20%E2%80%98living%20in%20sin%E2%80%99%20is%20possible%20to%20outsource%20in%20a%20society%20which%20polices%20the%20bedrooms%20adults%20can%20or%20cannot%20enter%20via%20marriage.%20Middle%20class%20%E2%80%98woke%E2%80%99%20rhetoric%20has%20been%20quick%20to%20cancel%20the%20anachronism%20of%20one%20but%20not%20the%20other.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statistical%20incidence%20of%20free%20spirits%20entering%20bohemian%20relationships%20with%20partners%20they%20are%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eallowed%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20marry%2C%20remains%20next%20to%20negligible%20in%20India.%20The%20regulatory%20harassment%20is%20really%20that%20of%20a%20separate%20minority%20of%20couples%20made%20up%20of%20predominantly%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Emixed%20caste%2C%20mixed%20faith%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%98wrong%E2%80%99%20partners%2C%20cohabiting%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98cringeworthy%E2%80%99%20manner.%20It%20makes%20political%20sense%20for%20the%20state%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20them%2C%20only%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20majoritarian%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20a%20parentally%20blessed%2C%20public%2C%20celebratory%20and%20endogamous%20union.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20for%20a%20government%20which%20wants%20to%20de-colonise%20India%2C%20the%20emphasis%20on%20marriage%20as%20the%20only%20healthy%20and%20normal%20sexual%2C%20cohabiting%20relationship%20possible%20between%20two%20adults%20%E2%80%93%20a%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20%E2%80%93%20remains%20an%20imperial%20legacy.%20Indeed%2C%20as%20my%20own%20research%20has%20shown%2C%20for%20the%20post%20Mutiny%20Crown%20government%20of%201857%2C%20the%20quest%20for%20uniformity%20was%20itself%20a%20punitive%20strategy%20by%20which%20to%20civilise%2C%20sanitise%20and%20subdue%20a%20defiant%20and%20extremely%20diverse%20native%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Esociety.%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEnforcing%20western%20conjugal%20adult%20norms%20of%20monogamy%20was%20predicated%2C%20however%2C%20on%20a%20colossal%20error%20%E2%80%93%20the%20confusion%20of%20the%20vast%20and%20bewildering%20variety%20of%20pre-pubertal%20sacramental%20%E2%80%98marriages%E2%80%99%20extant%20in%20India%20as%20unions%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20the%20same%20kind%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20as%20the%20rulers%E2%80%99%20own%20%E2%80%93%20legal%20contracts%20involving%20long%20engagements%2C%20mutual%20consent%20and%20the%20necessity%20for%20%E2%80%98love%E2%80%99%20to%20morally%20justify%20adult%20sexual%20cohabitation.%20In%20reality%2C%20the%20Victorian%20and%20the%20Hindu%20unions%20were%20not%20logically%20comparable%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rituals%20of%20marriage%20which%20all%20clean%2C%20caste%20Hindu%20girls%20underwent%2C%20bore%20no%20immediate%2C%20intrinsic%20or%20inherent%20connection%20with%20heterosexual%20love%20or%20even%20sexual%20consummation.%20Cross-culturally%20speaking%2C%20they%20were%20more%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20baptisms.%20Boys%20performed%20the%20sacred%20thread%20ceremony%2C%20girls%20performed%20the%20%E2%80%98marriage%E2%80%99%20ceremony%2C%20to%20count%20as%20full%20members%20of%20a%20particular%20caste%20society.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20is%20why%20even%20the%20%E2%80%98diverse%E2%80%99%20counter-intuitive%2C%20matrilineal%20customs%20of%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20to%20an%20absconding%20bridegroom%2C%20or%20to%20a%20deity%20or%20a%20sword%20or%20to%20a%20Brahmin%20guru%20from%20a%20different%20household%20%E2%80%93%20were%20all%20pre-pubertal%20and%20totally%20respectable%20community%20events.%20One%20only%20needs%20to%20have%20watched%20ITV%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EDownton%20Abbey%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20understand%20the%20colossal%20difference%20between%20the%20traditional%20variety%20of%20Hindu%20ceremonies%20and%20the%20uniform%20English%20understanding%20of%20marriage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENever%20ones%20to%20balk%20however%2C%20the%20imperial%20rulers%20rushed%20in%20where%20angels%20fear%20to%20tread.%20The%20obnoxious%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EContagious%20Diseases%20Act%20(CDA)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%201868%2C%20was%20unleashed%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20stamp%20out%20all%20but%20western%20styled%20nuclear%2C%20male%20headed%20family%20systems.%20Unions%20not%20focused%20around%20the%20heterosexual%20marital%20couple%20were%20stigmatised%20as%20perpetuators%20of%20promiscuity%2C%20polygamy%2C%20even%20%E2%80%9Chereditary%E2%80%9D%20prostitution.%20%E2%80%9CUnmarried%E2%80%9D%20women%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20abandoned%20widows%20or%20poorer%2C%20vagrant%2C%20less%20privileged%20single%20women%20%E2%80%93%20were%20incarcerated%20in%20Lock%20Hospitals%20as%20a%20source%20of%20venereal%20disease%20for%20British%20soldiers%20in%20cantonments%2C%20unaccompanied%20by%20wives%20under%20law.%20The%20Act%20however%20was%20condemned%20in%20Britain%20itself%20and%20finally%20repealed%20in%201886%20through%20the%20efforts%20of%20British%20suffragettes%2C%20its%20draconian%20business%20in%20India%20left%20half%20finished.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20second%20weapon%20aimed%20at%20standardising%20the%20Hindu%20family%20systems%20to%20meet%20the%20western%20norm%2C%20was%20the%20Age%20of%20Consent%20Bill%20(1891)%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20portray%20pre-pubertal%20marriage%20ceremonies%20as%20in%20fact%20perpetuating%20pederasty%20and%20criminal%20rape.%20But%20here%20too%2C%20after%20many%20long%20years%20of%20protest%20and%20Assembly%20deliberations%2C%20now%20by%20the%20upper%20castes%2C%20the%20government%20only%20managed%20an%20escalation%20of%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20from%20the%20existing%2010%20to%2012%20years!%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bill%E2%80%99s%20civilisational%20purpose%2C%20however%2C%20had%20been%20served%20%E2%80%93%20to%20demean%20the%20Hindus%20for%20bestiality%20towards%20child%20wives%20and%20women.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EStoked%20into%20nationalist%20anger%20over%20the%20Bill%2C%20Tilak%E2%80%99s%20Home%20Rule%20agitation%20(1916)%20and%20later%20The%20Sarada%20Act%20of%201928%2C%20under%20a%20triumphant%20native%20leadership%20now%2C%20put%20an%20end%20to%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20controversy%20by%20removing%20the%20justification%20for%20%E2%80%9Cchild%20marriage%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20bar%20was%20raised%20to%20a%20clear%20post-menarche%20age%20of%2014%20for%20women.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20child%20marriage%2C%20in%20its%20original%20pre-pubertal%20sacramental%20sense%2C%20is%20illicitly%20followed%20by%20some%20communities%20but%20by%20and%20large%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Esamskari%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20obligation%20that%20a%20girl%E2%80%99s%20first%20menarche%20must%20be%20preceded%20by%20a%20baptismal%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eceremony%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20marriage%20has%20thankfully%20lost%20its%20sacred%20force.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhy%2C%20then%2C%20the%20continual%20hiking%20of%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20post%20the%20Sarada%20Act%3F%20If%20we%20are%20to%20go%20by%20the%20authoritarian%20motivations%20of%20the%20imperial%20government%2C%20fixing%20biological%20age%20limits%20to%20the%20formal%20or%20informal%20practice%20of%20heterosexual%20coupling%20achieves%20%E2%80%9Cuniformity%E2%80%9D%20most%20efficiently.%20Currently%2C%20the%20minimum%20age%20of%20marriage%20%E2%80%93%2018%20for%20women%20%E2%80%93%20is%20threatening%20to%20go%20up%20to%20even%2021.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20criminalise%20more%20and%20more%20%E2%80%98wrong%E2%80%99%20unions%20as%20forms%20of%20%E2%80%9Cchild%20marriage%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20criminal%20law%20courts%E2%80%99%20repeated%20advisory%20that%20the%20government%20rethink%20lowering%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20has%20gone%20unheard.%20The%20persecution%20in%20Assam%20of%20many%20young%2C%20%E2%80%98differently%E2%80%99%20married%20men%2C%20as%20criminal%20rapists%20of%20technically%20underage%20but%20sexually%20mature%20wives%2C%20continues.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECharges%20of%20rape%20are%20largely%20initiated%20by%20parents%20of%20the%20girls%2C%20despite%20their%20protestations%20in%20court%20that%20the%20relationship%20was%20consensual%20and%20one%20of%20love.%20Now%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20UCC%2C%20the%20surveillance%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eadult%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20live%20in%20relationships%2C%20will%20bring%20in%20more%20and%20more%20%E2%80%98wrong%E2%80%99%20unions%20into%20the%20ambit%20of%20criminal%20prosecution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20post-colonial%2C%20largely%20virginal%2C%20legal%20marriage%20of%20today%20bears%20the%20marks%20of%20good%20old%20Indian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ejugaad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Thankfully%2C%20it%20is%20not%20child%20marriage%20any%20more.%20But%20equally%2C%20is%20it%20morally%20and%20not%20merely%20biologically%2C%20%E2%80%98adult%E2%80%99%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20astonishing%20statistic%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcensusindia.gov.in%2Fcensus.website%2Fdata%2Fcensus-tables%5C%22%3Ealmost%20the%20entire%20female%20population%20in%20the%20critical%20age%20group%20of%2025-29%20is%20married%3C%2Fa%3E%20(94.3%25%20according%20to%202001%20census%20and%2091.2%25%20in%202011)%2C%20points%20to%20traditional%20obligatory%2C%20family%20and%20community%20sentiments%20behind%20the%20%E2%80%98child%20marriage%E2%80%99%20of%20yore%20having%20carried%20over%20into%20the%20modern%2C%20adult%20avatar%20as%20well.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20UCC%E2%80%99s%20assumption%2C%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20gender%20rights%2C%20that%20young%20women%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20face%20a%20brutal%20fate%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20their%20live-in%20lovers%20is%20skewed.%20Matching%20the%20high%20percentage%20of%20the%20population%20of%20women%20that%20are%20married%20in%20India%2C%20is%20the%20other%2C%20dismally%20high%20percentage%20of%20married%20women%20who%20take%20their%20own%20lives%2C%20compared%20to%20other%20cultures%2C%20testifying%20to%20the%20pressure%20to%20not%20only%20marry%20but%20to%20stay%20married.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENational%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%E2%80%99s%20data%20on%20%E2%80%98accidental%20deaths%20and%20suicides%E2%80%99%20records%20that%20between%202014%20and%202020%2C%20women%20who%20were%20currently%20married%20accounted%20for%20a%20whopping%2063%C2%B71%25%20(28%2C085%20of%2044%2C498)%20suicide%20deaths%20among%20women%20in%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMarriage%20in%20India%20unfortunately%20does%20not%20ensure%20a%20more%20protected%2C%20happier%20young%20womanhood.%20The%20suffering%20of%20women%20routinely%20violated%2C%20killed%20and%20even%20burnt%20within%20the%20sacred%20legal%20confines%20of%20marriage%20cannot%20be%20denied%20a%20voice%20and%20strategically%20wished%20away%20to%20justify%20UCC%E2%80%99s%20uncalled%20for%20regulation%20of%20informal%20unions.%20Under%20criminal%20law%2C%20the%20death%20or%20harassment%20of%20a%20woman%20within%20the%20first%20seven%20years%20of%20marriage%20makes%20a%20man%20automatically%20vulnerable%20to%20charges%20of%20domestic%20violence%2C%20even%20murder%20and%20dowry%20death.%20The%20realities%20of%20a%20young%20bride%2C%20living%20with%20a%20husband%20who%20is%20really%20a%20stranger%2C%20under%20the%20control%20of%20his%20own%20parental%20household%2C%20is%20there%20for%20everyone%20to%20see%20in%20this%20legal%20prescription.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20India%2C%20almost%20all%20women%20are%20born%2C%20menstruate%20and%20marry%20under%20the%20benevolent%20and%20benign%20dictatorship%20of%20parents.%20In%20such%20a%20context%2C%20the%20Uttarakhand%20UCC%E2%80%99s%20determined%20attempt%20to%20put%20the%20screws%20on%20free%20consensual%20living%20together%2C%20based%20on%20love%20and%20mutual%20attraction%20between%20an%20adult%20man%20and%20woman%2C%20is%20not%20entirely%20surprising.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAmrit%20Srinivasan%20is%20a%20sociologist%2C%20formerly%20a%20Professor%20at%20the%20IIT-%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709308753000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F18112019%2FFEE464CC-1368-48CB-AF2D-1EA659E84547.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Futtrakhands-uniform-civil-code-is-a-mere-extension-of-highly-controlled-lives-indian-women-lead%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20India%2C%20