5Cn%3Ch4%3E%3Cb%3EFact%20check%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh4%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20the%20Siddaramaiah%20government%20begin%20taxing%20Hindu%20temples%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Siddaramaiah%20government%20did%20not%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20introduce%20the%20tax%20on%20Hindu%20temples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Common%20Pool%20Fund%20was%20started%20in%202003%20when%20the%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20%26amp%3B%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Act%2C%201997%20came%20into%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202011%2C%20Section%2017%20of%20this%20law%20was%20amended%20and%20a%20provision%20was%20made%20to%20collect%20a%20small%20portion%20of%20the%20funds%20generated%20by%20high%20income%20temples%20to%20provide%20assistance%20to%20low%20income%20temples%20under%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20B.S.%20Yediyurappa%20was%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20representing%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Common%20Pool%20Fund%20has%20been%20described%20in%20detail%20in%20Chapter%204%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20and%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Act%2C%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20State%20Dharmarika%20Parishad%20has%20the%20power%20to%20create%20a%20common%20pool%20fund%20in%20which%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20income%20of%20big%20temples%20and%20grants%20received%20from%20the%20state%20government%20would%20be%20contributed%20for%20the%20maintenance%20of%20small%20and%20low%20income%20Hindu%20temples%2C%20and%20religious%20institutions%20of%20Hindus%20falling%20within%20the%20Muzrai%20department.%20Grants%20were%20created%20to%20build%20orphanages%20for%20Hindus%2C%20construction%20of%20cowsheds%2C%20the%20study%20of%20the%20Hindu%20religion%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20amendment%20made%20in%202011%2C%20the%20tax%20rates%20on%20temples%20were%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E0%25%20of%20the%20income%20of%20temples%20whose%20annual%20income%20was%20less%20than%20Rs%205%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E5%25%20of%20the%20net%20income%20of%20temples%20whose%20annual%20income%20exceeded%20Rs%205%20lakh%20but%20did%20not%20exceed%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E10%25%20of%20the%20net%20income%20of%20temples%20whose%20annual%20income%20was%20more%20than%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20amendment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThere%20is%20no%20common%20pool%20fund%20for%20temples%20whose%20annual%20income%20is%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20temples%20with%20an%20annual%20income%20between%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%2C%20a%20total%20of%205%25%20of%20their%20annual%20income%20would%20go%20to%20the%20common%20pool%20fund.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20temples%20with%20an%20annual%20income%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20and%20above%2C%20a%20total%20of%2010%25%20would%20go%20to%20the%20common%20pool%20fund.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20source%20working%20in%20the%20Karnataka%20government%20shared%20a%20file%20with%20%3Cem%3EAlt%20News%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20documents%20the%20past%20and%20present%20changes%20in%20the%20Karnataka%20Hindu%20Religious%20Institutions%20%26amp%3B%20Charitable%20Endowments%20Act%201997%20Amendment%20Bill.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.altnews.in%2Fs%2FmfR7qE98r2b8ccp%5C%22%3EComplete%20file%3C%2Fa%3E)%20It%20can%20be%20clearly%20seen%20from%20the%20invocation%20of%20Section%2017%20of%20this%20law%20that%20the%20Common%20Pool%20Fund%20had%20been%20in%20force%20since%202003%2C%20and%20was%20changed%20in%202011%20when%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Yediyurappa%20was%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Karnataka.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20as%20well%2C%205%20to%2010%25%20of%20the%20total%20annual%20income%20of%20high%20income%20temples%20used%20to%20go%20to%20the%20common%20pool%20fund.%20In%20the%20later%20change%2C%20only%20the%20income%20ba